WEBVTT

00:00:05.806 --> 00:00:08.141 line:80%
[♪ pop music playing]

00:00:50.058 --> 00:00:53.770 line:80%
PERFECT CROWN

00:01:04.656 --> 00:01:05.782 line:80%
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

00:01:05.866 --> 00:01:07.784 line:80%
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

00:01:07.868 --> 00:01:09.619 line:80%
[♪ majestic music playing]

00:01:21.339 --> 00:01:22.924 line:80%
[narrator] <i>The unyielding throne of Joseon</i>

00:01:24.509 --> 00:01:26.303 line:80%
<i>stood firm for 600 years…</i>

00:01:35.896 --> 00:01:38.023 line:80%
<i>before fading</i>
<i>under the constitutional monarchy.</i>

00:01:40.358 --> 00:01:42.861 line:80%
<i>Though its prestige endured,</i>
<i>it became largely ceremonial.</i>

00:01:45.947 --> 00:01:47.115 line:80%
<i>Power became class.</i>

00:01:49.159 --> 00:01:50.452 line:80%
<i>Class became hereditary.</i>

00:01:51.870 --> 00:01:53.038 line:80%
<i>And it held on…</i>

00:01:54.998 --> 00:01:56.082 line:80%
<i>tenaciously.</i>

00:01:57.375 --> 00:01:58.585 line:80%
[chattering]

00:02:03.423 --> 00:02:04.591 line:80%
[student] Make way, make way.

00:02:04.674 --> 00:02:05.675 line:80%
I said, move.

00:02:06.426 --> 00:02:07.886 line:80%
2009 ROYAL ACADEMY
SPRING EXAM RANKING

00:02:07.969 --> 00:02:09.804 line:80%
TOP LAUREATE:
SEONG HUIJU, JUJAK HOUSE

00:02:09.888 --> 00:02:12.724 line:80%
SECOND-PLACE LAUREATE:
RYU MINSEOK, CHEONGNYONG HOUSE

00:02:13.308 --> 00:02:15.018 line:80%
It's that brat again?

00:02:16.895 --> 00:02:18.897 line:80%
[♪ dramatic music playing]

00:02:32.035 --> 00:02:33.036 line:80%
[gasps]

00:02:33.787 --> 00:02:35.080 line:80%
You said you'd win.

00:02:36.665 --> 00:02:38.041 line:80%
And yet you lost again.

00:02:38.875 --> 00:02:39.876 line:80%
[scoffs]

00:02:41.086 --> 00:02:43.213 line:80%
Only fools flail desperately over trifles.

00:02:44.172 --> 00:02:45.548 line:80%
Aren't you exhausted yet?

00:02:45.632 --> 00:02:46.633 line:80%
Hmm?

00:02:47.342 --> 00:02:48.468 line:80%
Was it hard for you?

00:02:49.344 --> 00:02:52.389 line:80%
I didn't find this exam difficult at all.

00:02:52.472 --> 00:02:53.890 line:80%
[clears throat]

00:02:53.974 --> 00:02:56.309 line:80%
You've lost. Learn to accept defeat.

00:02:57.560 --> 00:02:59.437 line:80%
Don't run your mouth
and embarrass yourself.

00:02:59.938 --> 00:03:01.398 line:80%
You're not even a noble.

00:03:01.481 --> 00:03:02.899 line:80%
Know your place.

00:03:02.983 --> 00:03:04.943 line:80%
Watch your mouth, you noble prick.

00:03:06.736 --> 00:03:08.238 line:80%
Do you want to be written up?

00:03:09.572 --> 00:03:10.573 line:80%
Damn it.

00:03:11.199 --> 00:03:13.535 line:80%
You should put some effort
into it next time, Minseok.

00:03:14.327 --> 00:03:15.328 line:80%
Okay?

00:03:15.412 --> 00:03:17.455 line:80%
How is it you lose every single time?

00:03:17.539 --> 00:03:19.541 line:80%
You're an esteemed nobleman, after all.

00:03:21.251 --> 00:03:22.836 line:80%
Just look at this mess of a uniform.

00:03:28.717 --> 00:03:30.051 line:80%
[foot thuds]

00:03:30.593 --> 00:03:33.013 line:80%
[principal] <i>Is Huiju the top laureate</i>
<i>for the ninth grade again?</i>

00:03:33.096 --> 00:03:34.806 line:80%
[clocks ticking]

00:03:36.141 --> 00:03:37.183 line:80%
Yes, sir.

00:03:38.393 --> 00:03:40.937 line:80%
The morale in Jujak House
must be through the roof.

00:03:41.646 --> 00:03:44.899 line:80%
[teacher chuckles]
Everyone's spirits are high.

00:03:46.651 --> 00:03:47.694 line:80%
Seong Huiju.

00:03:48.570 --> 00:03:50.697 line:80%
-Yes?
-Are you aware of our founding philosophy?

00:03:52.282 --> 00:03:54.951 line:80%
-Pardon?
-Why the Crown established this school.

00:03:56.286 --> 00:03:57.287 line:80%
Well…

00:03:58.621 --> 00:04:00.498 line:80%
Equal opportunity and…

00:04:00.582 --> 00:04:03.710 line:80%
That's right. Equal opportunity
was very much the objective.

00:04:04.335 --> 00:04:05.962 line:80%
Seonggyungwan is great and all,

00:04:06.046 --> 00:04:08.715 line:80%
but limiting admission
to noblemen's sons has obvious limits.

00:04:12.844 --> 00:04:13.887 line:80%
Right.

00:04:15.680 --> 00:04:17.515 line:80%
Do you know who invented this?

00:04:22.187 --> 00:04:23.354 line:80%
That's right.

00:04:23.438 --> 00:04:25.774 line:80%
A masterpiece of its era,
commissioned by King Sejong

00:04:25.857 --> 00:04:27.233 line:80%
and crafted by Jang Yeongsil.

00:04:28.234 --> 00:04:29.819 line:80%
-Isn't it? [chuckles]
-[chuckles]

00:04:30.820 --> 00:04:32.822 line:80%
He may have been the son of a courtesan,

00:04:33.823 --> 00:04:35.408 line:80%
but he had a brilliant mind.

00:04:36.868 --> 00:04:38.369 line:80%
[chuckles]

00:04:41.206 --> 00:04:42.957 line:80%
Here. Take this.

00:04:48.838 --> 00:04:50.673 line:80%
[♪ gentle music playing]

00:05:07.982 --> 00:05:13.404 line:80%
PERFECT CROWN

00:05:14.114 --> 00:05:15.198 line:20%
EPISODE 1

00:05:15.281 --> 00:05:16.825 line:20%
[Huiju] You said we'd win,

00:05:18.576 --> 00:05:19.661 line:20%
but we lost.

00:05:19.744 --> 00:05:21.287 line:20%
[stammers] Lost?

00:05:21.371 --> 00:05:23.206 line:20%
We remain the industry leader,

00:05:23.289 --> 00:05:25.834 line:20%
and we also ranked first
in the preference survey.

00:05:27.335 --> 00:05:30.338 line:20%
You know how underhanded
their promotional tactics can be.

00:05:30.421 --> 00:05:32.674 line:20%
They're offering 50% off
as part of their launch event.

00:05:33.174 --> 00:05:35.260 line:20%
And you know Lee Yungyeong,
who made a comeback?

00:05:35.343 --> 00:05:38.346 line:20%
They managed to create some buzz
with that celebrity endorsement.

00:05:38.429 --> 00:05:39.764 line:20%
[laughs]

00:05:41.182 --> 00:05:42.267 line:20%
So,

00:05:42.350 --> 00:05:44.185 line:20%
you're confirming we lost

00:05:44.936 --> 00:05:45.937 line:80%
in terms of sales.

00:05:47.230 --> 00:05:48.231 line:80%
My apologies, ma'am.

00:05:48.314 --> 00:05:49.607 line:80%
Let's start digging.

00:05:49.691 --> 00:05:51.526 line:80%
Who shall we dig into exactly?

00:05:51.609 --> 00:05:54.237 line:80%
Don't tell me you want us
to dig into their CEO.

00:05:54.320 --> 00:05:55.405 line:80%
That's asking for trouble.

00:05:55.488 --> 00:05:58.241 line:80%
That would be a complete waste of time.
[clicks tongue]

00:05:58.324 --> 00:05:59.659 line:80%
Of course.

00:05:59.742 --> 00:06:00.785 line:80%
[chuckling]

00:06:00.869 --> 00:06:03.246 line:80%
Lee Yungyeong turned us down
and became their spokesperson.

00:06:04.455 --> 00:06:05.832 line:80%
Dig into her.

00:06:05.915 --> 00:06:07.041 line:80%
Understood. Pardon?

00:06:07.125 --> 00:06:10.378 line:80%
When a single ad blows up like this,
there are bound to be issues.

00:06:10.461 --> 00:06:13.631 line:80%
Where there are issues, trouble follows.

00:06:14.716 --> 00:06:17.969 line:80%
It shouldn't be too difficult to spin them
into a full-blown media storm.

00:06:19.012 --> 00:06:21.514 line:80%
No… [clears throat]
…it shouldn't be difficult, but…

00:06:21.598 --> 00:06:23.474 line:80%
If it's not difficult, then do it.

00:06:24.058 --> 00:06:27.270 line:80%
Play dirty and cheap. [chuckles]

00:06:27.979 --> 00:06:29.731 line:80%
-Yes, ma'am.
-Logistics.

00:06:31.191 --> 00:06:32.317 line:80%
Yes, ma'am.

00:06:32.400 --> 00:06:34.110 line:80%
I'm the logistics manager.

00:06:34.194 --> 00:06:35.195 line:80%
What?

00:06:36.279 --> 00:06:37.697 line:80%
You two could be twins.

00:06:38.656 --> 00:06:39.657 line:80%
[all laugh]

00:06:40.575 --> 00:06:42.785 line:80%
Anyhow, let's cut outbound volume.

00:06:43.536 --> 00:06:45.371 line:80%
-By half.
-That much?

00:06:45.455 --> 00:06:49.042 line:80%
Spark fear of missing out in consumers
and push the products to sell out.

00:06:49.125 --> 00:06:50.210 line:80%
Make it go viral.

00:06:50.293 --> 00:06:51.794 line:80%
As quickly and loudly as possible.

00:06:51.878 --> 00:06:53.588 line:80%
-Yes, ma'am.
-Wait, hold on.

00:06:53.671 --> 00:06:57.717 line:80%
That's not as easy as it sounds.
The units have already been produced.

00:06:57.800 --> 00:06:59.260 line:80%
-Toss them.
-Pardon?

00:06:59.344 --> 00:07:01.846 line:80%
Bury them or burn them.

00:07:02.847 --> 00:07:05.058 line:80%
The possibilities are endless.

00:07:05.141 --> 00:07:07.310 line:80%
But we'd take a huge loss…

00:07:07.393 --> 00:07:09.395 line:80%
Gosh, look at our logistics manager.

00:07:10.271 --> 00:07:13.733 line:80%
Sounds like you save every penny
just to pinch it harder. [laughs]

00:07:17.612 --> 00:07:19.030 line:80%
Yeah. My goodness.

00:07:19.781 --> 00:07:22.867 line:80%
I hope all that saving
makes you ridiculously rich.

00:07:23.785 --> 00:07:25.119 line:80%
I will decide

00:07:25.203 --> 00:07:28.248 line:80%
what I do with my money.

00:07:28.998 --> 00:07:31.167 line:80%
-[clears throat]
-[gulps]

00:07:31.960 --> 00:07:33.503 line:80%
-[sighs]
-[phone beeping]

00:07:33.586 --> 00:07:36.297 line:80%
-Whose phone is that?
-Unbelievable.

00:07:36.381 --> 00:07:37.799 line:80%
That's five minutes. We're done.

00:07:37.882 --> 00:07:39.467 line:80%
Hold on. We have one more item.

00:07:39.550 --> 00:07:42.553 line:80%
Traffic downtown is already nuts.
You don't want to be late.

00:07:42.637 --> 00:07:44.806 line:80%
I get it! [clicks tongue]

00:07:44.889 --> 00:07:47.725 line:80%
Why did His Majesty
have to be born today of all days?

00:07:48.810 --> 00:07:49.978 line:80%
[sighs]

00:07:50.979 --> 00:07:52.897 line:80%
You all know I'll be at the palace today.

00:07:52.981 --> 00:07:56.859 line:80%
I'll be drumming up
some serious buzz for us.

00:07:57.443 --> 00:07:58.820 line:80%
So I expect all of you

00:07:59.654 --> 00:08:00.655 line:80%
to work just as hard.

00:08:01.572 --> 00:08:03.783 line:80%
-Yes, ma'am.
-Of course.

00:08:04.534 --> 00:08:05.785 line:80%
What exactly should we--

00:08:05.868 --> 00:08:08.162 line:80%
Write up articles. Articles.

00:08:08.246 --> 00:08:09.747 line:80%
-Articles.
-[Huiju] Yes. Articles.

00:08:09.831 --> 00:08:11.124 line:80%
[employee] Articles…

00:08:11.207 --> 00:08:15.420 line:80%
"Castle Group successor gets invited
to His Majesty's Royal Birthday Banquet."

00:08:15.920 --> 00:08:17.338 line:80%
[exclaims]

00:08:17.422 --> 00:08:19.048 line:80%
Killer headline, don't you think?

00:08:19.132 --> 00:08:20.425 line:80%
[assistant] You're the successor now?

00:08:20.508 --> 00:08:22.427 line:80%
-No.
-Then why did you lie?

00:08:22.510 --> 00:08:26.389 line:80%
The ones who claim
they're all that rarely are.

00:08:26.472 --> 00:08:28.975 line:80%
They all say it,
hoping to will it into existence.

00:08:30.435 --> 00:08:31.853 line:80%
Do you know nothing about PR?

00:08:57.712 --> 00:09:00.048 line:80%
THE ROYAL FAMILY GATHERS
FOR THE KING'S ROYAL BIRTHDAY

00:09:00.131 --> 00:09:02.383 line:80%
…PREPARES FOR
A ROYAL CELEBRATION…

00:09:02.467 --> 00:09:04.510 line:80%
ROYAL BIRTHDAY BANQUET
AT GYEONGBOKGUNG PALACE…

00:09:07.722 --> 00:09:09.223 line:80%
[shower running]

00:09:28.659 --> 00:09:31.788 line:80%
[court lady] Your Royal Highness,
you must make haste.

00:09:37.293 --> 00:09:38.961 line:80%
-Your Royal Highness!
-[aide] Excuse me.

00:09:42.173 --> 00:09:43.174 line:80%
[sighs]

00:09:45.968 --> 00:09:47.470 line:80%
[exhales]

00:09:47.553 --> 00:09:49.639 line:80%
I'll handle it from here. You all can go.

00:09:52.683 --> 00:09:55.144 line:80%
Your Royal Highness, it is Hyeon.

00:09:56.145 --> 00:09:57.271 line:80%
[prince] Come in.

00:09:58.689 --> 00:09:59.941 line:80%
[clears throat]

00:10:04.487 --> 00:10:06.155 line:80%
[♪ tense music playing]

00:10:31.055 --> 00:10:32.056 line:80%
Your Royal Highness.

00:10:32.598 --> 00:10:34.225 line:80%
Have you prepared a gift?

00:10:38.020 --> 00:10:39.647 line:80%
After seeing blood all morning…

00:10:42.859 --> 00:10:44.360 line:80%
[hammer cocks]

00:10:48.739 --> 00:10:50.241 line:80%
…I remain fervid.

00:10:54.745 --> 00:10:55.746 line:80%
[chuckles]

00:10:56.706 --> 00:10:58.458 line:80%
[chuckles]

00:10:58.541 --> 00:10:59.750 line:80%
Fervid, I see.

00:10:59.834 --> 00:11:01.752 line:80%
-Shall I get you some tea?
-No.

00:11:02.795 --> 00:11:05.298 line:80%
-[groans] I need to catch up on sleep.
-Wait.

00:11:06.632 --> 00:11:07.633 line:80%
Your Royal Highness,

00:11:08.134 --> 00:11:11.137 line:80%
as if hunting today were not bad enough,
now you wish to take a nap?

00:11:11.220 --> 00:11:12.680 line:80%
-That will not do.
-[inhales sharply]

00:11:12.763 --> 00:11:14.891 line:80%
-I mean, out of all days--
-Choi Hyeon.

00:11:16.684 --> 00:11:18.394 line:80%
Aide Choi Hyeon.

00:11:22.023 --> 00:11:23.524 line:80%
[groans]

00:11:23.608 --> 00:11:26.611 line:80%
But today is
His Majesty's Royal Birthday Banquet!

00:11:27.445 --> 00:11:28.446 line:80%
[sighs]

00:11:31.657 --> 00:11:32.992 line:80%
[paparazzo] Please wave this way!

00:11:33.075 --> 00:11:34.285 line:80%
[paparazzi clamoring]

00:11:35.703 --> 00:11:38.456 line:80%
-Look over here!
-Please look over here!

00:11:41.292 --> 00:11:43.711 line:80%
[reporter]
I'm currently standing outside the palace,

00:11:43.794 --> 00:11:45.880 line:80%
where the Royal Birthday Banquet
is being held.

00:11:45.963 --> 00:11:48.633 line:80%
Distinguished guests of the royal family

00:11:48.716 --> 00:11:51.093 line:80%
are arriving one after another.

00:11:52.678 --> 00:11:54.138 line:80%
[engine revs]

00:11:59.227 --> 00:12:00.728 line:80%
[tires screech]

00:12:12.615 --> 00:12:13.699 line:80%
[shutters clicking]

00:12:19.163 --> 00:12:21.123 line:80%
[♪ pop music playing]

00:12:32.426 --> 00:12:34.595 line:80%
[paparazzo]
Ms. Seong, please look over here!

00:12:56.909 --> 00:12:59.954 line:80%
Did Seong Huiju really wear red
to come to the palace?

00:13:00.454 --> 00:13:01.956 line:80%
You know she's a clout chaser.

00:13:02.039 --> 00:13:03.374 line:80%
Can't deny she's beautiful.

00:13:03.457 --> 00:13:05.042 line:80%
-Go on. Take pictures.
-All right.

00:13:05.585 --> 00:13:06.669 line:80%
Get to work.

00:13:26.105 --> 00:13:28.858 line:80%
[paparazzi cheering]

00:13:34.655 --> 00:13:36.907 line:80%
All right!
Ms. Seong has grabbed their attention.

00:13:36.991 --> 00:13:38.159 line:80%
What do we do now?

00:13:38.242 --> 00:13:39.493 line:80%
Now we begin!

00:13:39.577 --> 00:13:41.495 line:80%
Go on! Get to it! Hurry up!

00:13:41.579 --> 00:13:43.998 line:80%
We must sell out
of everything she's wearing!

00:13:44.081 --> 00:13:45.916 line:80%
Type faster!

00:13:46.000 --> 00:13:48.336 line:80%
<i>Find all the photos</i>
<i>and articles she's featured in.</i>

00:13:48.419 --> 00:13:49.837 line:80%
<i>You will find them if you look.</i>

00:13:49.920 --> 00:13:52.423 line:80%
<i>You must keep searching,</i>
<i>and you must type faster.</i>

00:13:52.506 --> 00:13:54.383 line:80%
<i>That's the spirit! We can do this, people!</i>

00:13:54.467 --> 00:13:55.593 line:80%
<i>We are Castle Group!</i>

00:13:55.676 --> 00:13:58.220 line:80%
SEONG HUIJU'S RED SUIT
STEALS THE SPOTLIGHT

00:14:00.431 --> 00:14:01.682 line:80%
#SEONG HUIJU, #RED SUIT

00:14:01.766 --> 00:14:02.933 line:80%
RETHINKING RED SUITS NOW…

00:14:03.017 --> 00:14:04.018 line:80%
…SOLD OUT ALREADY…

00:14:04.101 --> 00:14:06.187 line:20%
THE CUT OF THAT SUIT IS INSANE!

00:14:06.270 --> 00:14:08.272 line:80%
Seong Huiju's suit! Seong Huiju's bag!

00:14:08.356 --> 00:14:09.357 line:80%
Seong Huiju's shoes!

00:14:09.440 --> 00:14:10.608 line:80%
[person] That's so pretty.

00:14:10.691 --> 00:14:12.860 line:80%
Those are just too cute. I can't even.

00:14:13.486 --> 00:14:14.987 line:80%
[PR manager] <i>Sold out!</i>

00:14:15.071 --> 00:14:16.280 line:80%
SHE WEARS IT, IT SELLS OUT

00:14:16.364 --> 00:14:18.032 line:80%
[Huiju]
<i>"Castle Group successor gets invited</i>

00:14:18.115 --> 00:14:20.451 line:80%
<i>to His Majesty's Royal Birthday Banquet."</i>

00:14:24.288 --> 00:14:25.790 line:80%
[♪ pop music ends]

00:14:27.375 --> 00:14:29.293 line:80%
[♪ majestic music playing]

00:14:30.419 --> 00:14:31.671 line:80%
Have you been well?

00:14:54.402 --> 00:14:55.778 line:80%
That's her, right?

00:14:55.861 --> 00:14:58.280 line:80%
-The second child of Castle Group?
-Second? As if.

00:14:59.031 --> 00:15:01.367 line:80%
They didn't even know she existed
until she was ten.

00:15:01.450 --> 00:15:02.827 line:80%
[guest 1] What do you mean?

00:15:02.910 --> 00:15:04.704 line:80%
[guest 2] The mistress raised her,

00:15:04.787 --> 00:15:06.414 line:80%
and when she was about ten,

00:15:07.248 --> 00:15:08.708 line:80%
she was sent to Chairman Seong.

00:15:09.291 --> 00:15:11.335 line:80%
[guest 1] A commoner,
born out of wedlock, no less?

00:15:11.419 --> 00:15:12.420 line:80%
[guest 2] Yeah.

00:15:12.503 --> 00:15:15.089 line:80%
[guest 3] That would explain
her various shortcomings.

00:15:15.172 --> 00:15:16.590 line:80%
No sense of honor or dignity.

00:15:16.674 --> 00:15:18.384 line:80%
Obnoxious and without a shred of sense.

00:15:18.467 --> 00:15:19.552 line:80%
So on and so forth.

00:15:20.386 --> 00:15:21.679 line:80%
In short, she's a psycho?

00:15:21.762 --> 00:15:22.763 line:80%
[guests chuckling]

00:15:26.851 --> 00:15:27.852 line:80%
[gasps]

00:15:30.980 --> 00:15:32.273 line:80%
Cheers.

00:15:32.356 --> 00:15:33.399 line:80%
[chuckles]

00:15:33.983 --> 00:15:35.025 line:80%
[scoffs]

00:15:36.235 --> 00:15:38.529 line:80%
[guests scoffing]

00:15:47.955 --> 00:15:51.751 line:80%
Wow, is that CEO Seong,
the industry's runner-up?

00:15:52.376 --> 00:15:54.128 line:80%
Excuse me. I'll take one of those.

00:15:54.211 --> 00:15:55.212 line:80%
Thank you.

00:15:56.088 --> 00:15:58.132 line:80%
I know you can hear me.

00:15:58.215 --> 00:15:59.592 line:80%
Then hear this. Get lost.

00:15:59.675 --> 00:16:00.968 line:80%
[sucking teeth]

00:16:01.051 --> 00:16:03.596 line:80%
Show some respect to your brother.
[clicks tongue]

00:16:03.679 --> 00:16:06.515 line:80%
This is why people call you uncultured.

00:16:06.599 --> 00:16:09.351 line:80%
I thought you at least possessed
some business prowess, but…

00:16:09.435 --> 00:16:11.020 line:80%
[laughs]

00:16:11.103 --> 00:16:13.189 line:80%
I heard your sales slipped recently.

00:16:14.148 --> 00:16:15.608 line:80%
I just don't understand it.

00:16:16.901 --> 00:16:19.361 line:80%
[sighs] Rumors have spread far and wide.

00:16:19.987 --> 00:16:21.155 line:80%
I know.

00:16:21.697 --> 00:16:22.865 line:80%
Far and wide, right?

00:16:22.948 --> 00:16:24.575 line:80%
[laughs]

00:16:24.658 --> 00:16:27.077 line:80%
We don't have any flashy ad campaigns.

00:16:27.703 --> 00:16:28.788 line:80%
No discounts, either.

00:16:29.705 --> 00:16:31.999 line:80%
Despite all your stunts
like the ad campaign, virality,

00:16:32.082 --> 00:16:35.169 line:80%
and even the half-off sales event,
my brand still took

00:16:35.252 --> 00:16:37.922 line:80%
the top spot in the preference survey,
surpassing yours.

00:16:38.005 --> 00:16:40.174 line:80%
-[chuckles]
-Common knowledge, apparently.

00:16:41.842 --> 00:16:44.261 line:80%
I'm concerned about pushback
on the high price point.

00:16:45.346 --> 00:16:47.431 line:80%
But cutting prices would just kill me.

00:16:47.515 --> 00:16:49.099 line:80%
It feels so bargain-bin.

00:16:50.434 --> 00:16:51.435 line:80%
Just like somebody.

00:16:51.519 --> 00:16:53.938 line:80%
What, "Bargain-bin"?

00:16:54.021 --> 00:16:55.314 line:80%
[sighs] Unbelievable.

00:16:55.397 --> 00:16:57.817 line:80%
Hey, that's just
your inferiority complex talking.

00:16:57.900 --> 00:17:00.361 line:80%
My… [laughs] …inferiority complex?

00:17:00.444 --> 00:17:01.821 line:80%
-Me?
-Yeah.

00:17:01.904 --> 00:17:03.197 line:80%
-Triggered by you?
-Yeah.

00:17:03.906 --> 00:17:06.617 line:80%
You're clearly obsessed
with luxury marketing

00:17:06.700 --> 00:17:08.828 line:80%
because deep inside, you're a knockoff.

00:17:08.911 --> 00:17:11.497 line:80%
I get you're trying hard
to cover up your lowly origins,

00:17:12.248 --> 00:17:15.793 line:80%
but please just try
to live a life benefiting your station.

00:17:16.627 --> 00:17:19.046 line:80%
[slurps] Stop glaring, you brat.

00:17:19.129 --> 00:17:20.840 line:80%
[clicks tongue] I'm your older brother.

00:17:20.923 --> 00:17:23.843 line:80%
I just hate seeing you like that
as your older brother.

00:17:23.926 --> 00:17:26.637 line:80%
Maybe we're only half,
but at the end of the day,

00:17:27.137 --> 00:17:28.848 line:80%
we're still siblings.

00:17:28.931 --> 00:17:30.891 line:80%
Hmm? Right?

00:17:32.059 --> 00:17:33.310 line:80%
Yapping away like a little lapdog.

00:17:33.394 --> 00:17:35.646 line:80%
What? Why you--

00:17:35.729 --> 00:17:39.275 line:80%
If you're going to yap like that,
at least wear a leash.

00:17:39.358 --> 00:17:41.986 line:80%
A leash I could pull to choke you with.

00:17:42.069 --> 00:17:44.154 line:80%
[coughing]

00:17:44.238 --> 00:17:46.574 line:80%
Also, it's
"a life befitting your station,"

00:17:46.657 --> 00:17:49.827 line:80%
not "a life benefiting your station,"
you moron.

00:17:50.327 --> 00:17:53.914 line:80%
[coughing]

00:17:56.917 --> 00:17:58.836 line:80%
We will now make our way
to Junghwajeon Hall.

00:18:01.672 --> 00:18:03.883 line:80%
[coughing]

00:18:11.807 --> 00:18:13.017 line:80%
[sighs]

00:18:15.019 --> 00:18:17.062 line:80%
We're a package deal here.

00:18:19.148 --> 00:18:20.316 line:80%
Just two-bit peddlers.

00:18:22.610 --> 00:18:23.611 line:80%
[sighs]

00:18:44.214 --> 00:18:46.800 line:80%
[sighs]
I can't see anything from back here.

00:18:47.301 --> 00:18:48.844 line:80%
That pillar isn't helping.

00:18:50.721 --> 00:18:52.014 line:80%
[sighs]

00:19:01.649 --> 00:19:03.150 line:80%
-[thuds]
-[guests muttering]

00:19:03.233 --> 00:19:04.443 line:80%
[brother] Oh, boy.

00:19:09.406 --> 00:19:10.407 line:80%
[chuckles]

00:19:15.871 --> 00:19:16.872 line:80%
Your Majesty.

00:19:38.894 --> 00:19:40.854 line:80%
Why aren't they starting?

00:19:41.355 --> 00:19:43.524 line:80%
Grand Prince I-AN isn't here yet.

00:19:45.025 --> 00:19:46.527 line:80%
What's taking him so long?

00:19:51.949 --> 00:19:53.617 line:80%
[♪ gentle music playing]

00:20:14.304 --> 00:20:15.848 line:80%
[person] Announcing Grand Prince I-AN.

00:21:13.238 --> 00:21:15.157 line:80%
Hey, look at what he's wearing.

00:21:15.240 --> 00:21:16.408 line:80%
Is he here for a hunt?

00:21:16.492 --> 00:21:17.493 line:80%
Shut it.

00:21:27.294 --> 00:21:28.587 line:80%
My apologies, Your Majesty.

00:21:30.297 --> 00:21:31.298 line:80%
Queen Mother Yun.

00:21:31.381 --> 00:21:32.841 line:80%
Uncle!

00:21:33.842 --> 00:21:35.260 line:80%
Please accept my warmest wishes.

00:21:35.344 --> 00:21:36.887 line:80%
What manner of attire is this?

00:21:39.348 --> 00:21:41.975 line:80%
His Majesty bestowed
this silk upon me some time ago.

00:21:42.726 --> 00:21:43.977 line:80%
Is it not to your liking?

00:21:44.061 --> 00:21:45.646 line:80%
It looks so good on you--

00:21:45.729 --> 00:21:47.147 line:80%
You must observe decorum.

00:21:48.398 --> 00:21:50.776 line:80%
Hunting season has passed.

00:21:52.694 --> 00:21:54.655 line:80%
Do you believe hunting
is limited to a season?

00:21:57.658 --> 00:21:58.909 line:80%
You can lecture me later.

00:22:01.161 --> 00:22:02.246 line:80%
I must take my seat…

00:22:05.207 --> 00:22:06.583 line:80%
for all of them to take theirs.

00:22:09.670 --> 00:22:10.796 line:80%
[inhales]

00:22:10.879 --> 00:22:12.464 line:80%
[♪ tense music playing]

00:22:37.656 --> 00:22:39.449 line:80%
[♪ celebratory music playing]

00:22:41.577 --> 00:22:43.036 line:80%
[reporter] <i>The nation has been celebrating</i>

00:22:43.120 --> 00:22:45.330 line:80%
<i>in honor of His Majesty's royal birthday.</i>

00:22:46.123 --> 00:22:48.333 line:80%
<i>Events at Cheonggyecheon Stream</i>
<i>and Gwanghwamun</i>

00:22:48.417 --> 00:22:50.377 line:80%
<i>are set to carry on throughout the night.</i>

00:22:51.253 --> 00:22:54.131 line:80%
<i>With the day designated a public holiday,</i>
<i>heavy traffic is expected</i>

00:22:54.214 --> 00:22:55.841 line:80%
<i>as crowds head out for the break.</i>

00:22:55.924 --> 00:22:57.217 line:80%
[crowd cheering]

00:23:01.930 --> 00:23:04.266 line:80%
<i>Following the ceremony</i>
<i>featuring the formal greetings,</i>

00:23:04.349 --> 00:23:07.394 line:80%
<i>the second half will begin</i>
<i>alongside a Nakhwa Nori display.</i>

00:23:07.477 --> 00:23:10.105 line:80%
[♪ soft music playing]

00:23:10.189 --> 00:23:13.650 line:80%
After His Majesty writes down a wish
and presents it to Grand Prince I-AN,

00:23:13.734 --> 00:23:17.070 line:80%
His Royal Highness will commence
the Nakhwa Nori.

00:23:24.411 --> 00:23:27.497 line:80%
Good health for Queen Mother.

00:23:28.749 --> 00:23:31.752 line:80%
Good health for Uncle.

00:23:37.257 --> 00:23:41.762 line:80%
Happiness for the people.

00:23:44.598 --> 00:23:46.767 line:80%
Well done, Your Majesty.

00:24:22.261 --> 00:24:25.222 line:80%
[crowd gasping, exclaiming]

00:24:27.474 --> 00:24:29.226 line:80%
[cheering, applauding]

00:24:39.987 --> 00:24:42.114 line:80%
[guests chattering, laughing]

00:24:43.657 --> 00:24:46.660 line:80%
-Hello, Prime Minister Min.
-It's nice to see you, sir.

00:24:46.743 --> 00:24:48.870 line:80%
-Hello there.
-I'm always rooting for you.

00:24:49.955 --> 00:24:51.873 line:80%
[guest] Thank you for all your hard work.

00:24:51.957 --> 00:24:54.126 line:80%
-[Min] It's nice to see you.
-[guest 2] So handsome.

00:24:54.209 --> 00:24:55.419 line:80%
My goodness.

00:25:01.049 --> 00:25:02.050 line:80%
[Min] Seong Huiju.

00:25:02.134 --> 00:25:03.552 line:80%
[Huiju] Ooh.

00:25:05.095 --> 00:25:08.307 line:80%
-Should I call you Prime Minister Min?
-[sighs] Come on now.

00:25:08.390 --> 00:25:09.850 line:80%
Don't. That'd be so awkward.

00:25:09.933 --> 00:25:11.435 line:80%
[chuckles]

00:25:11.518 --> 00:25:14.146 line:80%
Look at that rosy pink floral overcoat.

00:25:14.229 --> 00:25:15.856 line:80%
You didn't come to play.

00:25:16.732 --> 00:25:20.110 line:80%
The Cabinet would bite my head off
if I showed up here in civilian clothes.

00:25:21.820 --> 00:25:23.697 line:80%
Where were you?
I couldn't find you earlier.

00:25:23.780 --> 00:25:26.241 line:80%
I was all the way in the back.

00:25:26.325 --> 00:25:28.118 line:80%
And you must've been in the front row.

00:25:28.201 --> 00:25:29.828 line:80%
How's the front row? Is it fun?

00:25:30.454 --> 00:25:33.081 line:80%
Don't get me started.
It was so boring I almost fell asleep.

00:25:33.749 --> 00:25:34.750 line:80%
It was pure torture.

00:25:34.833 --> 00:25:36.626 line:80%
-[scoffs]
-[Min chuckles]

00:25:38.628 --> 00:25:40.756 line:80%
-You've been crushing it.
-Me?

00:25:40.839 --> 00:25:43.300 line:80%
I hear Castle Beauty's US rollout
is going well.

00:25:43.383 --> 00:25:44.384 line:80%
[Huiju] Hmm.

00:25:44.468 --> 00:25:46.303 line:80%
I'm sure everyone is secretly shocked.

00:25:46.386 --> 00:25:49.139 line:80%
Taeju tried and failed
at the same venture two years ago.

00:25:49.222 --> 00:25:50.265 line:80%
Come on.

00:25:50.349 --> 00:25:52.351 line:80%
You know
I'm in a different league than him.

00:25:52.434 --> 00:25:54.936 line:80%
-[sighs, chuckles]
-[chuckles]

00:25:57.105 --> 00:25:59.900 line:80%
But… was this outfit intentional?

00:25:59.983 --> 00:26:01.193 line:80%
Yeah.

00:26:01.276 --> 00:26:02.694 line:80%
Why? You don't like it?

00:26:02.778 --> 00:26:04.154 line:80%
[Min sighs]

00:26:04.237 --> 00:26:06.281 line:80%
I thought red wasn't permitted
in the palace.

00:26:06.365 --> 00:26:10.077 line:80%
[scoffs] Who cares?
It's not like I'm breaking any laws.

00:26:10.160 --> 00:26:13.205 line:80%
You should still be careful.
It could lead to controversy.

00:26:13.288 --> 00:26:15.290 line:80%
What's so bad about a little controversy?

00:26:15.374 --> 00:26:17.334 line:80%
Nobody knows who Seong Taeju is,

00:26:17.417 --> 00:26:19.086 line:80%
but everyone knows Seong Huiju.

00:26:19.169 --> 00:26:21.421 line:80%
They know I'm the CEO of Castle Beauty

00:26:21.505 --> 00:26:23.423 line:80%
and that I'm an illegitimate child.

00:26:24.216 --> 00:26:26.009 line:80%
[sucks teeth] Hey.

00:26:27.594 --> 00:26:28.595 line:80%
[Hyeon] Prime Minister Min.

00:26:39.689 --> 00:26:40.857 line:80%
I need to go.

00:26:40.941 --> 00:26:43.193 line:80%
Make some time for me soon.
Let's grab a bite.

00:26:43.276 --> 00:26:44.986 line:80%
As long as you don't show up
in that. [chuckles]

00:26:45.654 --> 00:26:46.655 line:80%
[laughs]

00:26:46.738 --> 00:26:49.324 line:80%
That's enough teasing. [chuckles]

00:26:50.492 --> 00:26:51.493 line:80%
Bye.

00:26:52.828 --> 00:26:54.871 line:80%
-Prime Minister Min.
-[Min] Hello.

00:26:57.040 --> 00:26:58.333 line:80%
[sighs]

00:26:58.417 --> 00:27:00.627 line:80%
[♪ calm music playing]

00:27:12.431 --> 00:27:13.432 line:80%
Your Royal Highness.

00:27:25.068 --> 00:27:27.487 line:80%
How many times
have I told you not to run off alone?

00:27:27.571 --> 00:27:28.613 line:80%
Why?

00:27:28.697 --> 00:27:31.074 line:80%
Are you afraid
I might be assassinated quietly?

00:27:31.575 --> 00:27:34.035 line:80%
I'm more worried
about your aide dying from stress.

00:27:34.119 --> 00:27:35.745 line:80%
You disappeared, and he came running…

00:27:35.829 --> 00:27:36.955 line:80%
[clears throat]

00:27:38.331 --> 00:27:41.084 line:80%
You should just be more careful.
You're precious cargo.

00:27:41.168 --> 00:27:42.544 line:80%
[clicks tongue]

00:27:42.627 --> 00:27:44.004 line:80%
Why aren't you getting married?

00:27:45.046 --> 00:27:46.173 line:80%
That's random.

00:27:46.256 --> 00:27:49.885 line:80%
Half the maidens at the banquet
couldn't stop staring at you.

00:27:49.968 --> 00:27:51.928 line:80%
What's this now?

00:27:52.012 --> 00:27:53.930 line:80%
The other half… No.

00:27:54.473 --> 00:27:56.600 line:80%
More than half of them were staring at me.

00:27:56.683 --> 00:27:57.767 line:80%
[chuckles]

00:27:59.394 --> 00:28:00.604 line:80%
[scoffs]

00:28:01.730 --> 00:28:02.731 line:80%
So?

00:28:03.356 --> 00:28:05.484 line:80%
You want to marry me off
and steal the spotlight?

00:28:06.318 --> 00:28:07.527 line:80%
[sighs]

00:28:07.611 --> 00:28:08.987 line:80%
Quite the opposite, actually.

00:28:09.988 --> 00:28:11.114 line:80%
Pardon?

00:28:11.198 --> 00:28:12.866 line:80%
It appears I'll soon be married.

00:28:14.576 --> 00:28:15.577 line:80%
You will?

00:28:16.703 --> 00:28:19.956 line:80%
My sister-in-law presses me
to take a spouse day after day.

00:28:20.582 --> 00:28:21.958 line:80%
[clicks tongue, inhales]

00:28:22.042 --> 00:28:23.752 line:80%
It'll happen sooner rather than later.

00:28:25.837 --> 00:28:28.381 line:80%
That will make your life quite difficult.

00:28:30.091 --> 00:28:31.092 line:80%
Me?

00:28:31.176 --> 00:28:33.220 line:80%
I'd have to leave the palace
if I got married.

00:28:33.303 --> 00:28:36.223 line:80%
It'll be difficult to serve as regent
from outside the palace.

00:28:36.723 --> 00:28:39.726 line:80%
But His Majesty,
at the tender age of eight,

00:28:39.809 --> 00:28:41.728 line:80%
cannot attend to state affairs.

00:28:43.230 --> 00:28:44.231 line:80%
[sighs]

00:28:45.315 --> 00:28:46.650 line:80%
The duties you dumped on me,

00:28:47.901 --> 00:28:49.736 line:80%
including the various charity events,

00:28:49.819 --> 00:28:51.363 line:80%
hosting of diplomatic delegations,

00:28:51.446 --> 00:28:54.199 line:80%
visiting international organizations,
cultural heritage management,

00:28:55.700 --> 00:28:58.745 line:80%
and the unbearably dull
military ceremonies

00:28:58.828 --> 00:29:01.081 line:80%
will all fall to you once more.

00:29:01.164 --> 00:29:02.541 line:80%
[chuckles]

00:29:02.624 --> 00:29:03.750 line:80%
What could go wrong?

00:29:05.252 --> 00:29:06.253 line:80%
That will not do.

00:29:06.336 --> 00:29:07.337 line:80%
[clears throat]

00:29:08.380 --> 00:29:10.215 line:80%
No. Absolutely not. [chuckles]

00:29:11.508 --> 00:29:12.801 line:80%
That cannot happen.

00:29:12.884 --> 00:29:16.096 line:80%
We're already short on royals
able to attend to state affairs.

00:29:16.179 --> 00:29:17.222 line:80%
If you leave, we won't have--

00:29:17.305 --> 00:29:19.349 line:80%
-Then block it.
-What?

00:29:20.976 --> 00:29:22.310 line:80%
Use your veto power.

00:29:22.394 --> 00:29:24.938 line:80%
A royal marriage requires
the approval of the Cabinet.

00:29:25.981 --> 00:29:27.065 line:80%
The Royal Family Act.

00:29:28.400 --> 00:29:29.401 line:80%
[gasps]

00:29:33.655 --> 00:29:34.656 line:80%
[scoffs]

00:29:38.451 --> 00:29:40.579 line:80%
He could've just said that from the start.

00:29:40.662 --> 00:29:42.581 line:80%
Did he need to make me sweat?
[clicks tongue]

00:29:46.710 --> 00:29:48.086 line:80%
Seriously?

00:29:48.920 --> 00:29:51.548 line:80%
I can't believe they really cut off
cell service for this.

00:29:51.631 --> 00:29:53.592 line:80%
-[exclaims]
-[I-AN] Who goes there?

00:29:57.512 --> 00:29:58.555 line:80%
Your Royal Highness.

00:30:01.349 --> 00:30:03.351 line:80%
[♪ gentle music playing]

00:30:12.861 --> 00:30:13.862 line:80%
Name.

00:30:21.161 --> 00:30:22.287 line:80%
Please forgive me.

00:30:23.163 --> 00:30:24.998 line:80%
I seem to have lost my way.

00:30:26.207 --> 00:30:27.292 line:80%
Your name.

00:30:29.586 --> 00:30:30.712 line:80%
It is Seong Huiju.

00:30:31.755 --> 00:30:32.881 line:80%
Affiliation.

00:30:34.007 --> 00:30:35.842 line:80%
I am not a member of the palace staff.

00:30:39.387 --> 00:30:40.930 line:80%
Why is an outsider to the court…

00:30:42.849 --> 00:30:44.851 line:80%
loitering in an area…

00:30:47.604 --> 00:30:48.730 line:80%
not open to the public?

00:30:52.776 --> 00:30:55.737 line:80%
If you're gone in the count of three,
I'll overlook it.

00:30:56.821 --> 00:30:57.822 line:80%
Really?

00:31:01.409 --> 00:31:03.536 line:80%
That much I can do for my junior alum.

00:31:04.746 --> 00:31:06.289 line:80%
[sighs] That makes sense…

00:31:08.375 --> 00:31:10.168 line:80%
-Pardon?
-One.

00:31:11.378 --> 00:31:12.921 line:80%
-Two.
-[explosion]

00:31:15.256 --> 00:31:16.257 line:80%
[Huiju] What was that?

00:31:17.425 --> 00:31:18.468 line:80%
You stay here.

00:31:19.010 --> 00:31:21.471 line:80%
[♪ tense music playing]

00:31:21.554 --> 00:31:23.181 line:80%
[clamoring]

00:31:41.074 --> 00:31:43.284 line:80%
[court lady] Your Majesty! [sobbing]

00:31:45.829 --> 00:31:47.038 line:80%
[gasps]

00:31:49.874 --> 00:31:50.875 line:80%
[exhales]

00:31:52.585 --> 00:31:54.421 line:80%
[clamoring continues]

00:32:00.427 --> 00:32:01.678 line:80%
Are you unharmed?

00:32:03.263 --> 00:32:04.305 line:80%
What about His Majesty?

00:32:09.144 --> 00:32:10.395 line:80%
[Yun] Do you once more seek…

00:32:12.397 --> 00:32:14.607 line:80%
the life of another sovereign?

00:32:23.032 --> 00:32:24.033 line:80%
[King] Queen Mother!

00:32:26.911 --> 00:32:27.912 line:80%
[sighs]

00:32:28.663 --> 00:32:29.664 line:80%
Your Majesty.

00:32:32.709 --> 00:32:34.461 line:80%
Are you all right?

00:32:44.220 --> 00:32:45.555 line:80%
[Min] <i>Manage the optics.</i>

00:32:46.306 --> 00:32:49.142 line:80%
Keep the press under control
to prevent any conspiracy theories.

00:32:49.726 --> 00:32:51.311 line:80%
Aren't we taking this too lightly?

00:32:51.394 --> 00:32:52.729 line:80%
No need to overthink it.

00:32:52.812 --> 00:32:54.522 line:80%
There were no injuries or fatalities.

00:32:56.733 --> 00:32:59.319 line:80%
The late King passed away in a fire
three years ago.

00:32:59.986 --> 00:33:02.572 line:80%
The monarchy has only recently stabilized.

00:33:02.655 --> 00:33:03.656 line:80%
And now, another fire?

00:33:03.740 --> 00:33:05.742 line:80%
[sighs] That won't do at all.

00:33:11.372 --> 00:33:12.874 line:80%
It shouldn't be over already.

00:33:13.708 --> 00:33:14.793 line:80%
Why…

00:33:14.876 --> 00:33:16.002 line:80%
Hold on.

00:33:16.085 --> 00:33:17.587 line:80%
Don't tell me you just walked out.

00:33:17.670 --> 00:33:18.797 line:80%
What?

00:33:18.880 --> 00:33:19.881 line:80%
Oh.

00:33:19.964 --> 00:33:22.050 line:80%
Tell me you didn't just leave
to draw attention.

00:33:23.426 --> 00:33:25.261 line:80%
I couldn't even if I tried.

00:33:25.762 --> 00:33:27.555 line:80%
-Why not?
-There was an incident.

00:33:27.639 --> 00:33:29.057 line:80%
You caused an incident?

00:33:29.140 --> 00:33:30.183 line:80%
Seriously? [clicks tongue]

00:33:30.266 --> 00:33:32.435 line:80%
-There was a fire.
-A fire?

00:33:32.519 --> 00:33:34.521 line:80%
Wait. A fire?

00:33:34.604 --> 00:33:37.106 line:80%
What about the Grand Prince? Is he okay?

00:33:38.691 --> 00:33:39.984 line:80%
Ms. Do.

00:33:40.068 --> 00:33:41.528 line:80%
Are you a fan of Prince I-AN?

00:33:42.737 --> 00:33:44.030 line:80%
Me?

00:33:44.989 --> 00:33:45.990 line:80%
[scoffs]

00:33:48.243 --> 00:33:49.285 line:80%
I mean…

00:33:53.373 --> 00:33:56.084 line:80%
[reporter] <i>An explosion has occurred</i>
<i>at Junghwajeon Hall.</i>

00:33:56.167 --> 00:33:58.962 line:80%
<i>It occurred during</i>
<i>the Royal Birthday Banquet,</i>

00:33:59.045 --> 00:34:03.216 line:80%
<i>but fortunately,</i>
<i>no casualties have been reported.</i>

00:34:03.299 --> 00:34:05.176 line:80%
<i>The police and fire department…</i>

00:34:08.137 --> 00:34:09.681 line:80%
[Ms. Do] Is there some bad blood?

00:34:10.390 --> 00:34:11.391 line:80%
What?

00:34:11.474 --> 00:34:14.978 line:80%
Grand Prince I-AN also attended
the Royal Academy of Korea.

00:34:15.061 --> 00:34:17.856 line:80%
I thought you might've been
bullied or something.

00:34:17.939 --> 00:34:19.190 line:80%
You're so hostile toward him.

00:34:19.274 --> 00:34:20.692 line:80%
[scoffs]

00:34:20.775 --> 00:34:21.901 line:80%
Yeah, right.

00:34:23.194 --> 00:34:25.947 line:80%
Do I look like someone
who would be bullied?

00:34:26.030 --> 00:34:27.073 line:80%
[chuckles]

00:34:27.156 --> 00:34:28.157 line:80%
That's true.

00:34:29.075 --> 00:34:30.535 line:80%
Then why do you hate him so much?

00:34:31.995 --> 00:34:32.996 line:80%
Just because.

00:34:35.206 --> 00:34:36.291 line:80%
He's obnoxious.

00:34:38.126 --> 00:34:40.128 line:80%
[♪ gentle music playing]

00:34:44.299 --> 00:34:46.467 line:80%
Please work. Come on.

00:34:47.927 --> 00:34:48.970 line:80%
Please.

00:34:49.804 --> 00:34:51.055 line:80%
[sighs]

00:35:11.242 --> 00:35:12.243 line:80%
[sighs]

00:35:20.335 --> 00:35:21.544 line:80%
[sighs]

00:35:24.047 --> 00:35:25.048 line:80%
[sighs]

00:35:31.262 --> 00:35:32.263 line:80%
[I-AN] Who goes there?

00:35:34.766 --> 00:35:36.184 line:80%
[♪ gentle music playing]

00:35:49.614 --> 00:35:53.159 line:80%
If you've done wrong,
you must accept a fair punishment.

00:35:53.826 --> 00:35:56.204 line:80%
Don't disgrace yourself
by getting caught in flight.

00:35:56.287 --> 00:35:57.622 line:80%
Name.

00:36:03.419 --> 00:36:04.545 line:80%
It's Seong Huiju.

00:36:05.129 --> 00:36:06.339 line:80%
Affiliation.

00:36:08.633 --> 00:36:11.344 line:80%
Jujak House. Ninth grade.

00:36:11.427 --> 00:36:13.137 line:80%
You know you violated school regulations.

00:36:13.221 --> 00:36:16.516 line:80%
I needed more training time.
The exhibition match is coming up--

00:36:16.599 --> 00:36:18.393 line:80%
Are you a man of virtue or of profit?

00:36:20.645 --> 00:36:21.646 line:80%
[sighs]

00:36:21.729 --> 00:36:23.940 line:80%
Students under tenth grade are prohibited

00:36:24.023 --> 00:36:25.858 line:80%
from leaving the dormitory after 11 p.m.

00:36:25.942 --> 00:36:28.361 line:80%
Violation of this rule
results in 20 demerit points.

00:36:28.444 --> 00:36:30.655 line:80%
Use of facilities
outside designated training hours

00:36:30.738 --> 00:36:32.657 line:80%
requires prior approval
from the principal.

00:36:32.740 --> 00:36:35.201 line:80%
Violation of this rule
results in 10 demerit points.

00:36:35.284 --> 00:36:37.245 line:80%
-In total…
-And Your Royal Highness?

00:36:38.204 --> 00:36:39.872 line:80%
You are here too, are you not?

00:36:40.707 --> 00:36:42.667 line:80%
Will you receive demerit points as well?

00:36:50.550 --> 00:36:52.093 line:80%
I'm here with approval.

00:36:56.305 --> 00:36:57.974 line:80%
ARCHERY RANGE USAGE APPROVAL

00:36:59.392 --> 00:37:00.518 line:80%
How'd you get this?

00:37:00.601 --> 00:37:04.272 line:80%
After all that talk about students getting
carried away for the exhibition match

00:37:04.355 --> 00:37:07.525 line:80%
and the archery range not being
meant for individual training?

00:37:13.406 --> 00:37:16.534 line:80%
I got this key from Ryu Minseok,
Cheongnyong House, ninth grade.

00:37:16.617 --> 00:37:18.494 line:80%
-Ryu Minseok?
-Yes.

00:37:18.578 --> 00:37:20.830 line:80%
He was shamelessly bragging
about having this key,

00:37:20.913 --> 00:37:21.998 line:80%
so I stole it.

00:37:22.081 --> 00:37:23.374 line:80%
[sighs]

00:37:23.458 --> 00:37:26.335 line:80%
I'm not sure why an individual
had a key to this archery range

00:37:26.419 --> 00:37:28.755 line:80%
when it's not a place
for individual training.

00:37:30.548 --> 00:37:32.258 line:80%
[sighs]

00:37:32.341 --> 00:37:35.011 line:80%
But seeing how easily
you obtained this approval notice,

00:37:36.012 --> 00:37:38.389 line:80%
I guess it was only out of reach for me.

00:37:41.184 --> 00:37:43.519 line:80%
So do not lecture me
about demerit points or whatever.

00:37:43.603 --> 00:37:44.604 line:80%
I intend

00:37:45.229 --> 00:37:47.231 line:80%
to enjoy every opportunity

00:37:48.024 --> 00:37:49.150 line:80%
my enemy enjoys.

00:37:49.233 --> 00:37:50.818 line:80%
You wish to stoop to their level?

00:37:50.902 --> 00:37:53.029 line:80%
I'd rather play dirty and win

00:37:53.112 --> 00:37:55.406 line:80%
than play clean and lose.

00:38:02.413 --> 00:38:03.456 line:80%
[scoffs]

00:38:18.930 --> 00:38:20.098 line:80%
[scoffs]

00:38:21.891 --> 00:38:23.059 line:80%
So obnoxious.

00:38:26.854 --> 00:38:28.189 line:80%
[sighs]

00:38:45.164 --> 00:38:48.292 line:80%
[court lady] Your Royal Highness.
The Queen Mother has arrived.

00:38:52.088 --> 00:38:53.089 line:80%
Escort her in.

00:39:03.891 --> 00:39:05.601 line:20%
IN TIMES OF PEACE,
DO NOT FORGET DANGER

00:39:05.685 --> 00:39:07.562 line:20%
IN TIMES OF PROSPERITY,
DO NOT FORGET RUIN

00:39:07.645 --> 00:39:09.397 line:20%
IN TIMES OF ORDER,
DO NOT FORGET CHAOS

00:39:21.200 --> 00:39:22.326 line:80%
Must I wait longer?

00:39:26.247 --> 00:39:27.248 line:80%
Grand Prince.

00:39:29.125 --> 00:39:30.293 line:80%
Yes?

00:39:31.669 --> 00:39:32.753 line:80%
About yesterday…

00:39:35.923 --> 00:39:36.924 line:80%
I regret my actions.

00:39:39.135 --> 00:39:40.887 line:80%
I was not in my right mind.

00:39:42.180 --> 00:39:44.265 line:80%
I feared some misfortune
had struck His Majesty.

00:39:44.348 --> 00:39:46.392 line:80%
Prime Minister Min
has asked for the details

00:39:47.435 --> 00:39:49.187 line:80%
of how the Queen Mother

00:39:49.270 --> 00:39:52.607 line:80%
dared to strike the Grand Prince
and lash out with such unspeakable words.

00:39:54.901 --> 00:39:55.985 line:80%
So I hear.

00:40:00.740 --> 00:40:01.949 line:80%
Do not worry.

00:40:03.534 --> 00:40:05.494 line:80%
I shall tell him you took responsibility

00:40:06.329 --> 00:40:07.455 line:80%
and expressed remorse

00:40:08.998 --> 00:40:10.333 line:80%
for your actions.

00:40:13.878 --> 00:40:16.297 line:80%
No one shows concern for His Majesty.

00:40:17.506 --> 00:40:18.799 line:80%
The palace was on fire,

00:40:19.759 --> 00:40:21.385 line:80%
and the King almost died.

00:40:23.095 --> 00:40:26.349 line:80%
Yet all anyone seems to care about
is the scratch on your cheek.

00:40:26.432 --> 00:40:27.642 line:80%
Am I to blame for that?

00:40:27.725 --> 00:40:30.228 line:80%
Yes, you are. You are the regent.

00:40:38.736 --> 00:40:41.322 line:80%
His Majesty is a mere eight years of age.

00:40:41.405 --> 00:40:43.699 line:80%
Far too young
to be overseeing state affairs.

00:40:44.867 --> 00:40:46.285 line:80%
So my regency is unavoidable.

00:40:49.330 --> 00:40:50.581 line:80%
-I-AN…
-Furthermore,

00:40:52.166 --> 00:40:54.043 line:80%
a regent holds no special powers.

00:40:54.126 --> 00:40:55.461 line:80%
-I-AN!
-Politicians…

00:40:58.339 --> 00:41:00.007 line:80%
engage in politics.

00:41:02.134 --> 00:41:03.761 line:80%
Peddlers engage in business.

00:41:10.601 --> 00:41:12.270 line:80%
The monarchy remains passive.

00:41:14.105 --> 00:41:15.940 line:80%
Simply doing nothing…

00:41:18.651 --> 00:41:19.902 line:80%
is its sole duty.

00:41:23.614 --> 00:41:26.200 line:80%
Have you ever considered that
to be true power?

00:41:27.535 --> 00:41:28.786 line:80%
The politicians

00:41:29.370 --> 00:41:32.373 line:80%
burn with fervor
to claim a place at your side.

00:41:33.582 --> 00:41:35.793 line:80%
Because a single photo taken beside you

00:41:36.294 --> 00:41:39.213 line:80%
wields greater power than ten pledges
wrought with painstaking care.

00:41:40.006 --> 00:41:41.257 line:80%
And the business elites?

00:41:41.340 --> 00:41:45.136 line:80%
They hasten to attend to you
on every diplomatic tour.

00:41:45.219 --> 00:41:48.306 line:80%
The mere fact that you granted them
a place by your side

00:41:49.890 --> 00:41:52.018 line:80%
is enough to gain
the trust of their investors.

00:41:56.022 --> 00:41:57.064 line:80%
You eclipse…

00:42:00.860 --> 00:42:02.403 line:80%
the Crown itself.

00:42:08.993 --> 00:42:10.995 line:80%
[♪ emotional music playing]

00:42:14.165 --> 00:42:15.291 line:80%
Father.

00:42:15.374 --> 00:42:18.044 line:80%
I have received a 100 on my exam.

00:42:22.048 --> 00:42:24.258 line:80%
-Rise above such trifles.
-Sorry?

00:42:24.342 --> 00:42:26.469 line:80%
If it be remarkable,
it is but the natural order.

00:42:26.552 --> 00:42:27.762 line:80%
If it be lacking,

00:42:28.346 --> 00:42:30.222 line:80%
it is but a cause for shame.

00:42:30.306 --> 00:42:31.849 line:80%
But Father,

00:42:31.932 --> 00:42:35.227 line:80%
is diligence not
the duty of a man of virtue?

00:42:35.311 --> 00:42:38.689 line:80%
You are a Grand Prince
before you are a man of virtue.

00:42:38.773 --> 00:42:40.107 line:80%
I-SHIN

00:42:40.191 --> 00:42:42.068 line:80%
That is your new royal title.

00:42:43.611 --> 00:42:46.739 line:80%
My royal title is to change?

00:42:46.822 --> 00:42:49.325 line:80%
It is a reminder to remain true and just.

00:42:51.577 --> 00:42:53.954 line:80%
Do not stand in the way
of the Crown Prince.

00:43:07.468 --> 00:43:09.512 line:80%
This is your new royal title.

00:43:10.221 --> 00:43:11.764 line:80%
I-AN

00:43:13.599 --> 00:43:14.683 line:80%
Am I being…

00:43:17.686 --> 00:43:18.687 line:80%
rewarded again?

00:43:31.826 --> 00:43:32.827 line:80%
And so…

00:43:35.371 --> 00:43:36.747 line:80%
what do you seek from me?

00:43:38.040 --> 00:43:40.376 line:80%
That you be His Majesty's steadfast
pillar of support.

00:43:40.459 --> 00:43:42.086 line:80%
I already serve in that capacity.

00:43:43.045 --> 00:43:44.422 line:80%
Proceed to your nuptials.

00:43:47.842 --> 00:43:50.010 line:80%
Wed the woman of my choosing

00:43:51.262 --> 00:43:54.390 line:80%
and demonstrate your allegiance
to His Majesty and me.

00:44:05.943 --> 00:44:07.736 line:80%
[Huiju] <i>I told you I don't want to.</i>

00:44:09.613 --> 00:44:11.157 line:80%
[sighs] Fine.

00:44:11.240 --> 00:44:14.160 line:80%
Let's say I concede to everything,
and I do get married.

00:44:14.827 --> 00:44:18.831 line:80%
I am still an heir to a conglomerate,
so strategic M&amp;A is certainly important.

00:44:19.373 --> 00:44:22.001 line:80%
That's my role
in fortifying the family's legacy.

00:44:22.084 --> 00:44:24.628 line:80%
But the CEO of a mere subsidiary
simply will not do.

00:44:24.712 --> 00:44:26.255 line:80%
Do you think that makes any sense?

00:44:26.338 --> 00:44:27.506 line:80%
I'm Seong Huiju!

00:44:27.590 --> 00:44:29.049 line:80%
[Taeju] So what if you are?

00:44:29.717 --> 00:44:30.801 line:80%
Father, we're here.

00:44:31.469 --> 00:44:32.470 line:80%
Hey.

00:44:32.553 --> 00:44:34.430 line:80%
Must you be so loud?

00:44:34.513 --> 00:44:36.223 line:80%
All you do is bark day and night.

00:44:36.307 --> 00:44:38.517 line:80%
Hello, Father. Huiju.

00:44:38.601 --> 00:44:40.186 line:80%
Honey, you want a cup?

00:44:40.269 --> 00:44:42.396 line:80%
-So hot!
-You should be more careful, honey.

00:44:42.480 --> 00:44:43.772 line:80%
[exclaims]

00:44:43.856 --> 00:44:44.857 line:80%
You could've warned me.

00:44:48.235 --> 00:44:51.113 line:80%
Don't pester Father too much, Huiju.

00:44:51.197 --> 00:44:53.407 line:80%
He went to great lengths

00:44:53.491 --> 00:44:55.993 line:80%
to find a proper suitor for you.

00:44:56.076 --> 00:44:57.995 line:80%
[Mr. Seong sighs]

00:44:58.621 --> 00:44:59.788 line:80%
[scoffs]

00:45:00.289 --> 00:45:02.166 line:80%
So you two collaborated on this?

00:45:02.791 --> 00:45:04.585 line:80%
And this is the result?

00:45:04.668 --> 00:45:07.213 line:80%
A nobody who doesn't even make
the industry rankings?

00:45:07.296 --> 00:45:09.173 line:80%
Shall I use him as a trophy boyfriend?

00:45:09.256 --> 00:45:10.841 line:80%
Why you little…

00:45:11.717 --> 00:45:12.968 line:80%
[clicks tongue]

00:45:13.052 --> 00:45:14.845 line:80%
Our hands are tied.

00:45:15.513 --> 00:45:17.181 line:80%
When it comes to arranged marriages,

00:45:17.264 --> 00:45:20.267 line:80%
most families tend
to nitpick every detail.

00:45:20.351 --> 00:45:21.352 line:80%
"Every detail"?

00:45:23.479 --> 00:45:24.688 line:80%
"Every detail"?

00:45:25.356 --> 00:45:27.608 line:80%
[laughs]

00:45:27.691 --> 00:45:31.612 line:80%
So you also nitpicked "every detail"
and ended up with this loser?

00:45:31.695 --> 00:45:33.197 line:80%
That's strange.

00:45:33.280 --> 00:45:36.116 line:80%
With all that nitpicking,
you had to see the marriage was doomed.

00:45:36.200 --> 00:45:39.537 line:80%
-Hey, we married for love!
-Who cares what the in-laws' pet thinks?

00:45:39.620 --> 00:45:41.455 line:80%
-What was that?
-That's enough!

00:45:43.165 --> 00:45:45.501 line:80%
[sighs] She's just impossible.

00:45:46.418 --> 00:45:48.546 line:80%
As you said,
you'll eventually have to marry.

00:45:48.629 --> 00:45:50.172 line:80%
Who said I didn't want to marry?

00:45:50.256 --> 00:45:52.758 line:80%
I just don't want to marry
someone that far beneath me.

00:45:52.841 --> 00:45:53.884 line:80%
[Taeju scoffs]

00:45:53.968 --> 00:45:56.804 line:80%
[Huiju] Father, just be honest with me.

00:45:56.887 --> 00:45:59.056 line:80%
You want to take this chance
to get rid of me, no?

00:45:59.139 --> 00:46:02.059 line:80%
Because based on pure competence,
that jerk wouldn't stand a chance.

00:46:02.142 --> 00:46:05.020 line:80%
Hey, who wouldn't stand a chance?

00:46:05.104 --> 00:46:06.605 line:80%
You, obviously. Certainly not me!

00:46:08.065 --> 00:46:09.191 line:80%
[sighs]

00:46:10.776 --> 00:46:12.444 line:80%
I guess branding me illegitimate

00:46:12.528 --> 00:46:15.239 line:80%
and saddling me
with a useless brother wasn't enough?

00:46:15.322 --> 00:46:18.450 line:80%
Now you want to foist
an incompetent husband upon me as well?

00:46:20.119 --> 00:46:21.579 line:80%
This will not go

00:46:22.538 --> 00:46:23.872 line:80%
as you wish, Father.

00:46:25.457 --> 00:46:27.209 line:80%
I won't let that happen.

00:46:34.091 --> 00:46:35.217 line:80%
[Hyeon] <i>Nuptials?</i>

00:46:35.301 --> 00:46:37.344 line:80%
[stammers] Did you agree to it?

00:46:38.971 --> 00:46:40.431 line:80%
Maybe.

00:46:40.514 --> 00:46:41.515 line:80%
You're really going to?

00:46:44.560 --> 00:46:45.603 line:80%
Why not?

00:46:45.686 --> 00:46:47.479 line:80%
[Hyeon exclaims]

00:46:47.563 --> 00:46:51.108 line:80%
Since when did Your Royal Highness
become so obedient?

00:46:52.860 --> 00:46:54.778 line:80%
And since when have you grown so insolent?

00:46:57.656 --> 00:46:58.657 line:80%
My apologies, sir.

00:46:58.741 --> 00:47:01.243 line:80%
I'm just frustrated
with the situation, that's all.

00:47:01.327 --> 00:47:04.288 line:80%
I mean, all this time,
she was firmly against your nuptials.

00:47:04.371 --> 00:47:06.624 line:80%
And now, she wants you to get married?

00:47:06.707 --> 00:47:08.834 line:80%
To a woman she chooses, no less?

00:47:08.917 --> 00:47:10.377 line:80%
This is downright unreasonable.

00:47:10.461 --> 00:47:12.046 line:80%
[clicks tongue] Darn it.

00:47:13.672 --> 00:47:15.674 line:80%
[sighs]

00:47:20.137 --> 00:47:22.056 line:80%
We did this last year.

00:47:23.390 --> 00:47:25.225 line:80%
And this is what our competitor is doing.

00:47:26.685 --> 00:47:29.688 line:80%
[sighs] Did you need
more time or something?

00:47:30.522 --> 00:47:32.524 line:80%
Ms. Seong, the thing about PR is--

00:47:32.608 --> 00:47:35.152 line:80%
Don't tell me there are only
so many ways to spin it.

00:47:35.653 --> 00:47:38.197 line:80%
If that's your excuse, you should resign.

00:47:38.280 --> 00:47:40.199 line:80%
You're saying anyone could do your job.

00:47:40.282 --> 00:47:42.868 line:80%
If it's all the same,
why carry a bloated payroll?

00:47:42.951 --> 00:47:44.286 line:80%
My apologies.

00:47:45.371 --> 00:47:48.165 line:80%
We'll revise based on your feedback
and get back to you, ma'am.

00:47:49.458 --> 00:47:50.584 line:80%
[Huiju sighs]

00:47:53.087 --> 00:47:54.421 line:80%
[clicks tongue]

00:47:57.341 --> 00:47:59.259 line:80%
[door closes]

00:47:59.927 --> 00:48:01.679 line:80%
[sighs]

00:48:04.556 --> 00:48:05.557 line:80%
[Ms. Do] Here we go.

00:48:09.228 --> 00:48:10.896 line:80%
Drink some. It's lotus root tea.

00:48:16.276 --> 00:48:17.736 line:80%
Isn't this super bitter?

00:48:17.820 --> 00:48:20.531 line:80%
Come on. Just drink it.

00:48:20.614 --> 00:48:22.449 line:80%
It soothes pent-up anger.

00:48:23.033 --> 00:48:24.451 line:80%
I don't have any pent-up anger.

00:48:24.535 --> 00:48:26.912 line:80%
You've been riding the staff for days now.

00:48:29.832 --> 00:48:33.210 line:80%
Listen, I know you're on edge
with the marriage issue and all,

00:48:33.293 --> 00:48:35.379 line:80%
but don't drag personal issues
into the workplace.

00:48:35.963 --> 00:48:37.798 line:80%
-You look really petty.
-What?

00:48:37.881 --> 00:48:39.007 line:80%
"Petty"?

00:48:39.842 --> 00:48:41.969 line:80%
Who? Me?

00:48:42.052 --> 00:48:44.555 line:80%
Ms. Do. I am Seong Huiju!

00:48:45.180 --> 00:48:46.890 line:80%
Yeah, sure. Here.

00:48:49.143 --> 00:48:51.311 line:80%
-[huffs]
-Go on.

00:48:52.354 --> 00:48:53.355 line:80%
[in English] Drink it.

00:49:00.571 --> 00:49:01.739 line:80%
[in Korean] So bitter.

00:49:06.368 --> 00:49:10.164 line:80%
[♪ tense music playing]

00:49:19.715 --> 00:49:20.841 line:80%
[chuckles]

00:49:22.301 --> 00:49:23.427 line:80%
Your Royal Highness.

00:49:24.511 --> 00:49:25.512 line:80%
Lord INPYEONG.

00:49:26.638 --> 00:49:28.849 line:80%
It appears you are leaving the palace.

00:49:30.017 --> 00:49:31.977 line:80%
Yes, I am taking some time off.

00:49:32.561 --> 00:49:33.562 line:80%
"Time off"?

00:49:33.645 --> 00:49:37.232 line:80%
His Majesty's birthday preparations
had me held up in the palace for a while.

00:49:38.692 --> 00:49:39.777 line:80%
[sighs]

00:49:39.860 --> 00:49:42.488 line:80%
I intend to spend a few days resting
at my private residence.

00:49:42.571 --> 00:49:44.406 line:80%
Your private residence?

00:49:44.490 --> 00:49:47.326 line:80%
Then who will safeguard the palace,
Your Royal Highness?

00:49:47.409 --> 00:49:51.038 line:80%
What would we do
if you were to leave the palace alone

00:49:51.121 --> 00:49:52.414 line:80%
and misfortune befell you?

00:49:55.375 --> 00:49:57.503 line:80%
I thought you would welcome my absence.

00:50:01.715 --> 00:50:02.800 line:80%
[chuckles]

00:50:03.300 --> 00:50:05.594 line:80%
[laughs]

00:50:06.553 --> 00:50:09.056 line:80%
Perhaps I was under the wrong impression.

00:50:10.182 --> 00:50:12.059 line:80%
Please give my best to Queen Mother.

00:50:12.643 --> 00:50:16.855 line:80%
I was so excited about my time off
that I forgot to pay my respects.

00:50:19.191 --> 00:50:20.192 line:80%
[chuckles]

00:50:35.624 --> 00:50:38.085 line:80%
[Lord INPYEONG]
Is that what you said to him?

00:50:40.128 --> 00:50:41.964 line:80%
It was His Majesty's royal birthday.

00:50:43.298 --> 00:50:44.967 line:80%
He showed up late…

00:50:46.301 --> 00:50:47.553 line:80%
wearing a <i>cheollik.</i>

00:50:48.053 --> 00:50:50.097 line:80%
A fire even broke out.

00:50:50.180 --> 00:50:51.431 line:80%
That was all I-AN--

00:50:51.515 --> 00:50:52.516 line:80%
Your Majesty.

00:51:01.108 --> 00:51:03.068 line:80%
And the members of the royal family?

00:51:03.694 --> 00:51:06.864 line:80%
Despite tirelessly preaching propriety,
they do not dare utter

00:51:06.947 --> 00:51:09.700 line:80%
a single word of remonstrance
before the Grand Prince.

00:51:12.703 --> 00:51:14.705 line:80%
The people cherish the Grand Prince.

00:51:15.330 --> 00:51:16.707 line:80%
[scoffs]

00:51:16.790 --> 00:51:19.084 line:80%
Even after losing his parents and brother,

00:51:19.877 --> 00:51:22.671 line:80%
he continues to serve
as regent for his nephew,

00:51:22.754 --> 00:51:25.424 line:80%
safeguarding the Crown.

00:51:29.511 --> 00:51:31.263 line:80%
That is precisely the issue.

00:51:33.807 --> 00:51:35.976 line:80%
His Majesty is but a child,
throwing the disparity

00:51:36.560 --> 00:51:40.063 line:80%
between him and the Grand Prince
behind him into even starker relief.

00:51:51.950 --> 00:51:53.702 line:80%
KIM YEONGHUN,
CEO OF SEONGSAN TEXTILE

00:51:53.785 --> 00:51:54.870 line:80%
[Ms. Do] <i>None of them?</i>

00:51:55.370 --> 00:51:56.580 line:80%
[Huiju] Come on.

00:51:57.122 --> 00:52:00.626 line:80%
How are they any different
from the men Father picked?

00:52:00.709 --> 00:52:03.795 line:80%
At least be handsome if you're
a lost cause in the corporate rankings.

00:52:03.879 --> 00:52:05.797 line:80%
No money.

00:52:05.881 --> 00:52:07.549 line:80%
No looks to speak of.

00:52:07.633 --> 00:52:08.717 line:80%
Tsk, tsk, tsk.

00:52:09.676 --> 00:52:12.054 line:80%
What about politicians?
No candidates there?

00:52:12.721 --> 00:52:14.264 line:80%
Why is it all businessmen?

00:52:14.348 --> 00:52:16.725 line:80%
Politicians don't like mixing
with business people.

00:52:16.808 --> 00:52:19.561 line:80%
[scoffs] They love money
but hate business people?

00:52:19.645 --> 00:52:21.104 line:80%
Too much potential baggage.

00:52:21.188 --> 00:52:23.607 line:80%
-Illegal succession, tax evasion…
-What?

00:52:24.274 --> 00:52:25.359 line:80%
That's ridiculous.

00:52:25.442 --> 00:52:27.903 line:80%
Either way, politicians are a no-go.

00:52:27.986 --> 00:52:30.489 line:80%
They traditionally prefer aristocrats.

00:52:30.572 --> 00:52:32.407 line:80%
Aristocrats? You must be kidding.

00:52:32.491 --> 00:52:35.285 line:80%
Are we living in the Joseon era?
Are they trying to marry up?

00:52:35.369 --> 00:52:37.412 line:80%
<i>That's not something for you to say.</i>

00:52:38.872 --> 00:52:42.668 line:80%
[sighs] Ms. Do. Come on, Ms. Do!

00:52:43.418 --> 00:52:48.632 line:80%
I'm simply looking for someone
who matches my current status. That's all.

00:52:48.715 --> 00:52:50.592 line:80%
He doesn't need to be super impressive.

00:52:50.676 --> 00:52:52.678 line:80%
Just someone of my capability,

00:52:52.761 --> 00:52:56.181 line:80%
my means, and my beauty.

00:52:56.264 --> 00:52:57.891 line:80%
Is that too much to ask?

00:52:57.975 --> 00:53:00.519 line:80%
It's not like I'm looking
to marry into the royal…

00:53:01.228 --> 00:53:02.229 line:80%
family.

00:53:03.438 --> 00:53:05.440 line:80%
[♪ upbeat music playing]

00:53:09.486 --> 00:53:10.862 line:80%
Huh…

00:53:15.242 --> 00:53:17.869 line:80%
[♪ soft music playing]

00:53:24.001 --> 00:53:26.753 line:80%
[door opens, closes]

00:53:31.717 --> 00:53:33.468 line:80%
Didn't I warn you?

00:53:33.552 --> 00:53:34.594 line:80%
Just look at this.

00:53:36.263 --> 00:53:37.931 line:80%
I-AN,
THE 21ST-CENTURY PRINCE SUYANG

00:53:39.933 --> 00:53:42.144 line:80%
[stammers, huffs]

00:53:42.227 --> 00:53:44.688 line:80%
This is no time for doodling orchids.

00:53:44.771 --> 00:53:47.774 line:80%
I told you wearing the <i>cheollik</i>
was a bad idea.

00:53:47.858 --> 00:53:50.527 line:80%
Didn't I beg you to wear
proper court attire?

00:53:50.610 --> 00:53:52.654 line:80%
The Royal Secretariat
and Public Affairs Office

00:53:52.738 --> 00:53:54.448 line:80%
are outraged right now.

00:53:56.074 --> 00:53:58.952 line:80%
-And the public?
-They're in an uproar.

00:53:59.453 --> 00:54:02.289 line:80%
Is there any mention of the fire?

00:54:03.915 --> 00:54:04.916 line:80%
Pardon?

00:54:06.877 --> 00:54:07.919 line:80%
It appears my nickname

00:54:09.296 --> 00:54:10.589 line:80%
will be trending once more.

00:54:12.382 --> 00:54:16.261 line:20%
<i>The regent Grand Prince I-AN has recently</i>
<i>come under public scrutiny.</i>

00:54:16.344 --> 00:54:17.429 line:80%
Good morning.

00:54:17.512 --> 00:54:18.847 line:80%
Ms. Do, look at this.

00:54:18.930 --> 00:54:20.974 line:80%
[reporter]
<i>The controversy stems from his appearance.</i>

00:54:21.058 --> 00:54:23.685 line:80%
-<i>As the </i>cheollik<i> is considered informal…</i>
-Amazing, no?

00:54:23.769 --> 00:54:27.397 line:20%
<i>…many viewed it as inappropriate</i>
<i>for a Grand Prince at a royal celebration.</i>

00:54:27.481 --> 00:54:29.483 line:80%
He looks so sharp in that.

00:54:29.566 --> 00:54:31.985 line:80%
[reporter] <i>Members of the royal family</i>
<i>have voiced criticism.</i>

00:54:32.069 --> 00:54:35.530 line:20%
<i>They argue that preserving tradition</i>
<i>and decorum is the duty of the crown,</i>

00:54:35.614 --> 00:54:38.658 line:20%
<i>and that the Grand Prince's</i>
<i>recent bizarre behavior is unacceptable.</i>

00:54:38.742 --> 00:54:40.494 line:80%
"Bizarre"? That's taking it too far.

00:54:40.577 --> 00:54:42.245 line:80%
It's not like he was carrying a sword.

00:54:42.329 --> 00:54:45.999 line:80%
[reporter] <i>Political circles praised him</i>
<i>for putting practicality ahead of protocol</i>

00:54:46.083 --> 00:54:47.876 line:80%
<i>and modeling a modern monarchy.</i>

00:54:47.959 --> 00:54:49.753 line:80%
Politicians always take
Grand Prince I-AN's side.

00:54:49.836 --> 00:54:51.213 line:80%
Why?

00:54:51.296 --> 00:54:54.841 line:80%
Because the people are enamored
with the Grand Prince.

00:54:55.425 --> 00:54:57.427 line:80%
-He's so cool.
-Let's get back to work.

00:54:57.969 --> 00:55:00.097 line:80%
PRINCE I-AN IN CHEOLLIK
AT ROYAL BIRTHDAY BANQUET

00:55:02.057 --> 00:55:04.101 line:80%
-[knocks on door]
-[door opens]

00:55:11.149 --> 00:55:13.401 line:80%
Ah. His hype is next-level.

00:55:13.485 --> 00:55:15.570 line:80%
-[Huiju] What?
-[Ms. Do] Grand Prince I-AN.

00:55:15.654 --> 00:55:16.655 line:80%
[Huiju] Right.

00:55:16.738 --> 00:55:18.782 line:80%
The executive operations team
is buzzing about it.

00:55:20.242 --> 00:55:21.243 line:80%
Really?

00:55:23.411 --> 00:55:24.746 line:80%
What do you think of him?

00:55:26.081 --> 00:55:27.833 line:80%
[sighs]

00:55:27.916 --> 00:55:30.919 line:80%
PRINCE I-AN IN CHEOLLIK
AT ROYAL BIRTHDAY BANQUET

00:55:31.586 --> 00:55:32.838 line:80%
I think…

00:55:34.589 --> 00:55:35.924 line:80%
he's quite nice.

00:55:36.675 --> 00:55:37.884 line:80%
What?

00:55:40.428 --> 00:55:43.223 line:80%
[chuckles]

00:56:00.615 --> 00:56:01.616 line:80%
[grunts]

00:56:03.160 --> 00:56:04.703 line:80%
You told me not to pick them.

00:56:05.787 --> 00:56:06.955 line:80%
Well, I mean,

00:56:07.038 --> 00:56:10.041 line:80%
you mentioned that arranging flowers
can quiet a restless mind.

00:56:18.466 --> 00:56:19.467 line:80%
[sighs]

00:56:20.135 --> 00:56:23.013 line:80%
Why on earth are you remaining silent?
You should defend yourself.

00:56:23.096 --> 00:56:25.599 line:80%
Of course, it is true
that you violated decorum.

00:56:25.682 --> 00:56:27.267 line:80%
Proper court attire was a must.

00:56:28.143 --> 00:56:29.144 line:80%
But what can we do?

00:56:29.227 --> 00:56:31.146 line:80%
You remain so enamored with the spotlight.

00:56:31.229 --> 00:56:32.814 line:80%
But is that such a crime?

00:56:32.898 --> 00:56:36.193 line:80%
Is it so wrong to want
some attention in the 21st century?

00:56:36.276 --> 00:56:38.695 line:80%
Let's be real.
Court attire isn't the most flattering.

00:56:38.778 --> 00:56:40.864 line:80%
The <i>cheollik</i> is so much cooler, isn't it?

00:56:40.947 --> 00:56:43.158 line:80%
For one thing,
court attire has such a drab palette.

00:56:43.241 --> 00:56:44.409 line:80%
Such a grim brown.

00:56:44.492 --> 00:56:46.369 line:80%
Sure, it might suit someone like me

00:56:46.453 --> 00:56:49.164 line:80%
with a warm, golden complexion.

00:56:49.247 --> 00:56:52.209 line:80%
I can pull off colors like that just fine.

00:56:52.292 --> 00:56:55.420 line:80%
But on someone like Your Royal Highness,
with that icy cool tone,

00:56:55.503 --> 00:56:56.796 line:80%
it would just clash.

00:56:56.880 --> 00:56:58.757 line:80%
Give me a break already.

00:56:58.840 --> 00:57:00.550 line:80%
-That's enough.
-"That's enough."

00:57:02.719 --> 00:57:04.387 line:80%
-[sighs]
-[huffs]

00:57:06.640 --> 00:57:08.850 line:80%
-Tell them.
-Tell them what?

00:57:08.934 --> 00:57:10.644 line:80%
You meant no dishonor to His Majesty,

00:57:10.727 --> 00:57:13.313 line:80%
and you were only expressing
your simple, unassuming taste.

00:57:14.022 --> 00:57:15.565 line:80%
Just issue that statement already.

00:57:15.649 --> 00:57:17.442 line:80%
"Prince Suyang of the 21st-century"?

00:57:17.525 --> 00:57:19.152 line:80%
How does that make any sense?

00:57:20.904 --> 00:57:21.905 line:80%
[sighs]

00:57:24.699 --> 00:57:25.784 line:80%
Why not?

00:57:27.077 --> 00:57:28.370 line:80%
[Ms. Do] <i>You can't.</i>

00:57:28.954 --> 00:57:30.789 line:80%
-Why not?
-Of course, you can't.

00:57:30.872 --> 00:57:32.165 line:80%
Right.

00:57:34.292 --> 00:57:35.543 line:80%
And why is that exactly?

00:57:36.461 --> 00:57:37.587 line:80%
[sighs]

00:57:39.214 --> 00:57:40.215 line:80%
Are you drunk?

00:57:40.298 --> 00:57:41.633 line:80%
No.

00:57:41.716 --> 00:57:43.426 line:80%
Then what has gotten into you?

00:57:43.510 --> 00:57:46.554 line:80%
How can you even think
about marrying Prince I-AN?

00:57:47.430 --> 00:57:49.182 line:80%
Ms. Do, just think about it.

00:57:49.808 --> 00:57:51.309 line:80%
How many are as beautiful,

00:57:51.393 --> 00:57:53.186 line:80%
as intelligent,

00:57:53.270 --> 00:57:55.522 line:80%
and as wealthy as I am?

00:57:56.106 --> 00:57:58.858 line:80%
Where else could you find
such a match in this world?

00:57:58.942 --> 00:58:01.111 line:80%
[giggling]

00:58:01.194 --> 00:58:02.195 line:80%
Okay.

00:58:02.988 --> 00:58:04.197 line:80%
No one else knows, right?

00:58:04.281 --> 00:58:06.950 line:80%
-You didn't tell anyone else, right?
-You're the first.

00:58:08.076 --> 00:58:09.077 line:80%
Good thinking.

00:58:09.828 --> 00:58:12.956 line:80%
But I did submit a request
for a royal audience.

00:58:13.039 --> 00:58:15.625 line:80%
What? A royal audience request?

00:58:16.376 --> 00:58:18.420 line:80%
Where? How?

00:58:20.046 --> 00:58:21.256 line:80%
Royal audience requests?

00:58:21.756 --> 00:58:23.508 line:80%
I guess you really are trending.

00:58:23.591 --> 00:58:25.343 line:80%
The Prime Minister's Office reached out.

00:58:25.427 --> 00:58:27.387 line:80%
Lord Jeongseon is begging
for a meeting too.

00:58:27.470 --> 00:58:28.596 line:80%
Lord Jeongseon too?

00:58:28.680 --> 00:58:32.892 line:80%
He must be itching to chime in.
You know how talkative he is. [chuckles]

00:58:32.976 --> 00:58:33.977 line:80%
So nosy.

00:58:34.853 --> 00:58:35.937 line:80%
Oh, right!

00:58:36.021 --> 00:58:38.982 line:80%
Ms. Seong Huiju has also submitted
a request. How shall I proceed?

00:58:39.566 --> 00:58:42.152 line:80%
-Seong Huiju?
-Yes, the CEO of Castle Beauty.

00:58:42.235 --> 00:58:43.903 line:80%
The illegitimate-born of Castle Group.

00:58:48.158 --> 00:58:49.826 line:80%
YOUR AUDIENCE REQUEST
HAS BEEN REJECTED

00:58:49.909 --> 00:58:52.412 line:80%
Why was it rejected?
I haven't said a word yet.

00:58:53.246 --> 00:58:54.414 line:80%
It's okay, Ms. Seong.

00:58:54.914 --> 00:58:56.833 line:80%
An audience with Prince I-AN
is no easy feat.

00:58:56.916 --> 00:58:58.376 line:80%
And I'm easy?

00:58:58.460 --> 00:59:00.503 line:80%
I'm an incredibly busy person too.

00:59:00.587 --> 00:59:02.380 line:80%
Prince I-AN is currently a regent.

00:59:02.464 --> 00:59:04.132 line:80%
He's basically the king.

00:59:04.215 --> 00:59:07.260 line:80%
Plus, you said you didn't even write
a reason for the request.

00:59:07.344 --> 00:59:09.637 line:80%
What kind of king would give up his time
for someone like that?

00:59:09.721 --> 00:59:10.889 line:80%
Then what should I do?

00:59:10.972 --> 00:59:13.975 line:80%
Should I have written,
"I wish to marry you"?

00:59:14.768 --> 00:59:16.686 line:80%
Stop talking about
that damn marriage, okay?

00:59:16.770 --> 00:59:19.064 line:80%
I feel like I'm about to
get arrested any minute.

00:59:21.524 --> 00:59:22.609 line:80%
Hold on.

00:59:26.446 --> 00:59:27.447 line:80%
No way.

00:59:28.948 --> 00:59:30.241 line:80%
Is he playing hard to get?

00:59:30.325 --> 00:59:31.576 line:80%
[thunderclap]

00:59:34.037 --> 00:59:36.498 line:80%
He totally is. [scoffs]

00:59:52.263 --> 00:59:54.307 line:80%
Have we not heard from Grand Prince I-AN?

00:59:54.808 --> 00:59:56.976 line:80%
No, both the Royal Secretariat

00:59:57.060 --> 00:59:59.562 line:80%
and Lord Jeongseon
are pressing him on the matter.

01:00:00.355 --> 01:00:03.191 line:80%
But he has even turned down
Prime Minister Min's audience request.

01:00:05.485 --> 01:00:08.363 line:80%
Is this his way of saying
he remains completely unfazed?

01:00:13.410 --> 01:00:16.121 line:80%
[Hyeon] You're practically climbing
into that book at this rate.

01:00:17.205 --> 01:00:18.248 line:80%
[sighs]

01:00:19.249 --> 01:00:21.835 line:80%
Why did you ask for this food?

01:00:21.918 --> 01:00:23.294 line:80%
Did I do something wrong?

01:00:23.795 --> 01:00:24.879 line:80%
You eat it.

01:00:26.506 --> 01:00:27.715 line:80%
[chuckles]

01:00:28.633 --> 01:00:29.926 line:80%
Seriously?

01:00:31.261 --> 01:00:33.388 line:80%
I didn't know you cared for me so much.

01:00:34.347 --> 01:00:35.515 line:80%
Thank you for the food.

01:00:37.517 --> 01:00:38.518 line:80%
Mmm.

01:00:38.601 --> 01:00:41.479 line:80%
Yes, eat that and stop talking.

01:00:41.563 --> 01:00:42.564 line:80%
Huh?

01:00:42.647 --> 01:00:43.773 line:80%
All your nagging

01:00:44.649 --> 01:00:46.359 line:80%
is drowning out the sound of rain.

01:00:46.985 --> 01:00:47.986 line:80%
Yes, sir.

01:00:50.822 --> 01:00:52.490 line:80%
But this is important…

01:00:55.660 --> 01:00:58.538 line:80%
Ms. Seong has submitted
another request for a royal audience.

01:00:58.621 --> 01:01:00.081 line:80%
How shall I respond this time?

01:01:00.165 --> 01:01:01.166 line:80%
-Again?
-Yes.

01:01:01.249 --> 01:01:03.334 line:80%
I rejected it due to scheduling conflicts.

01:01:03.418 --> 01:01:05.378 line:80%
But she submitted
another request right away.

01:01:05.462 --> 01:01:07.422 line:80%
With a different name, no less.

01:01:08.006 --> 01:01:09.466 line:80%
-What does that mean?
-[scoffs]

01:01:09.549 --> 01:01:13.928 line:80%
The first request clearly stated,
"Seong Huiju from Castle Beauty."

01:01:14.012 --> 01:01:18.183 line:80%
This time, she put, "Castle Group
Seong Hyeonguk's second daughter."

01:01:18.850 --> 01:01:20.143 line:80%
[sighs]

01:01:20.226 --> 01:01:21.227 line:80%
Reject it.

01:01:21.311 --> 01:01:23.730 line:80%
YOUR AUDIENCE REQUEST
HAS BEEN REJECTED

01:01:25.732 --> 01:01:26.983 line:80%
Again?

01:01:27.942 --> 01:01:30.570 line:80%
[laughs]

01:01:30.653 --> 01:01:32.822 line:80%
Is he trying to get me riled up?

01:01:33.448 --> 01:01:34.532 line:80%
Unbelievable.

01:01:35.783 --> 01:01:37.243 line:80%
Have some.

01:01:37.327 --> 01:01:39.120 line:80%
We all work to fill our bellies, don't we?

01:01:39.204 --> 01:01:40.538 line:80%
Go on.

01:01:47.504 --> 01:01:48.505 line:80%
What's this?

01:01:49.547 --> 01:01:51.090 line:80%
-It's delicious.
-Good, right?

01:01:52.008 --> 01:01:53.676 line:80%
It just opened across the street.

01:01:53.760 --> 01:01:55.970 line:80%
The whole team orders
from there frequently.

01:01:56.471 --> 01:01:57.514 line:80%
Hey.

01:01:58.056 --> 01:02:01.935 line:80%
Tell them to share the treats they find
instead of just gorging themselves!

01:02:03.353 --> 01:02:06.105 line:80%
It'd be best if we didn't
have to work so late.

01:02:06.189 --> 01:02:08.858 line:80%
[sighs] God, this is beyond infuriating.

01:02:08.942 --> 01:02:10.818 line:80%
So what if he's a grand prince?

01:02:21.829 --> 01:02:24.874 line:80%
[inhales deeply, sighs]

01:02:24.958 --> 01:02:27.168 line:80%
Maybe it's because
I didn't put down a reason?

01:02:30.505 --> 01:02:33.007 line:80%
[sighing]

01:02:40.765 --> 01:02:41.933 line:80%
ROYAL AUDIENCE REQUEST

01:02:42.016 --> 01:02:43.893 line:80%
<i>Your Royal Highness,</i>

01:02:43.977 --> 01:02:47.230 line:80%
<i>Castle Group,</i>
<i>under the benevolent care of the Crown,</i>

01:02:47.313 --> 01:02:50.483 line:80%
<i>has continued to achieve</i>
<i>remarkable growth and development,</i>

01:02:50.567 --> 01:02:52.777 line:80%
<i>attaining the honor</i>
<i>of being the top conglomerate…</i>

01:02:54.654 --> 01:02:55.947 line:80%
[inhales sharply]

01:02:56.531 --> 01:02:58.825 line:80%
Ah, is this a bit too much?

01:03:06.124 --> 01:03:10.378 line:80%
<i>I sincerely pledge to further</i>
<i>the nation's development,</i>

01:03:10.461 --> 01:03:13.089 line:80%
<i>and I hereby request</i>
<i>an audience.</i> [chuckles]

01:03:13.172 --> 01:03:15.508 line:80%
<i>I patiently await the sagacious counsel</i>

01:03:15.592 --> 01:03:17.260 line:80%
<i>of Your Royal Highness.</i>

01:03:17.343 --> 01:03:20.263 line:80%
"Executive Director of Castle Group,

01:03:20.805 --> 01:03:23.933 line:80%
Seong Huiju."

01:03:26.019 --> 01:03:27.353 line:80%
SUBMIT

01:03:28.730 --> 01:03:30.189 line:80%
YOUR REQUEST HAS BEEN SUBMITTED

01:03:30.898 --> 01:03:31.899 line:80%
Ha!

01:03:34.444 --> 01:03:36.779 line:80%
[whispers]
Seriously, what's gotten into her?

01:03:36.863 --> 01:03:37.905 line:80%
[sighs]

01:03:43.494 --> 01:03:45.830 line:80%
[Hyeon] Your Royal Highness, Ms. Seong…

01:03:45.913 --> 01:03:47.081 line:80%
-[I-AN] Reject it.
-Yes, sir.

01:03:47.665 --> 01:03:49.417 line:80%
-Your Royal Highness.
-Reject it.

01:03:49.500 --> 01:03:50.501 line:80%
Yes, sir.

01:03:51.377 --> 01:03:52.920 line:80%
-Reject it.
-Yes, sir.

01:03:53.755 --> 01:03:54.756 line:80%
Got it.

01:03:55.548 --> 01:03:56.633 line:80%
Ms. Seong--

01:03:56.716 --> 01:03:57.884 line:80%
-Reject it!
-Yes, sir!

01:04:01.095 --> 01:04:03.723 line:80%
Ms. Seong continues
to submit her requests.

01:04:03.806 --> 01:04:05.350 line:80%
How much longer must I…

01:04:05.433 --> 01:04:07.060 line:20%
REJECT IT

01:04:07.644 --> 01:04:09.354 line:80%
-Your Royal Highness.
-Reject it.

01:04:09.437 --> 01:04:10.563 line:80%
But wait--

01:04:10.647 --> 01:04:12.190 line:80%
-Reject it!
-Rejected.

01:04:18.029 --> 01:04:19.989 line:80%
<i>I reject your request for an audience.</i>

01:04:23.826 --> 01:04:26.287 line:80%
[screams]

01:04:26.371 --> 01:04:27.497 line:80%
Oh, my goodness.

01:04:28.456 --> 01:04:31.167 line:80%
Jeez, what's wrong with her?

01:04:38.549 --> 01:04:41.177 line:80%
[I-AN] If you're gone
in the count of three, I'll overlook it.

01:04:42.887 --> 01:04:44.138 line:80%
Really?

01:04:47.058 --> 01:04:49.268 line:80%
That much I can do for my junior alum.

01:04:54.232 --> 01:04:55.358 line:80%
[sighs]

01:04:58.695 --> 01:05:01.114 line:80%
[♪ soft music playing]

01:05:08.204 --> 01:05:10.581 line:80%
[Hyeon] She has already submitted
over five requests.

01:05:11.165 --> 01:05:12.583 line:80%
With another new name this time?

01:05:12.667 --> 01:05:14.877 line:80%
Yes, she put down "Junior alum" this time.

01:05:17.004 --> 01:05:18.423 line:80%
-"Junior alum"?
-Yes.

01:05:19.549 --> 01:05:22.885 line:80%
She requests the esteemed counsel
of her senior alum this time.

01:05:22.969 --> 01:05:24.095 line:80%
[laughs]

01:05:24.178 --> 01:05:26.973 line:80%
What's this now? Are you two alumni?

01:05:27.598 --> 01:05:28.891 line:80%
[chuckles]

01:05:29.809 --> 01:05:31.394 line:80%
I assume it's another rejection?

01:05:32.145 --> 01:05:33.146 line:80%
Grant it.

01:05:34.272 --> 01:05:35.356 line:80%
Pardon?

01:05:35.440 --> 01:05:36.816 line:80%
How can I say no

01:05:38.234 --> 01:05:39.402 line:80%
to a junior alum in need?

01:05:42.196 --> 01:05:43.364 line:80%
[computer chimes]

01:05:47.952 --> 01:05:49.746 line:80%
YOUR AUDIENCE REQUEST
HAS BEEN ACCEPTED

01:05:50.913 --> 01:05:52.623 line:80%
[sighs, chuckles]

01:05:54.167 --> 01:05:56.377 line:80%
[laughs]

01:05:56.461 --> 01:05:57.545 line:80%
It worked.

01:05:58.629 --> 01:06:00.631 line:80%
[♪ hopeful music playing]

01:06:40.338 --> 01:06:41.339 line:80%
[chuckles]

01:06:44.425 --> 01:06:45.635 line:80%
[Yun] <i>Who did you say was there?</i>

01:06:46.219 --> 01:06:48.554 line:80%
[court lady] Executive Director
Seong Huiju of Castle Group.

01:06:53.309 --> 01:06:56.062 line:80%
You said you had a mole
planted at his residence, right?

01:06:56.145 --> 01:06:58.356 line:80%
-Yes, Your Majesty.
-Can I trust her?

01:06:58.439 --> 01:07:01.400 line:80%
Yes. You may call upon her at any time.

01:07:02.610 --> 01:07:04.612 line:80%
[♪ ominous music playing]

01:07:51.242 --> 01:07:52.368 line:80%
[chuckles]

01:07:54.370 --> 01:07:55.872 line:80%
I am not sure what to call you.

01:08:01.586 --> 01:08:02.837 line:80%
You seem to go by many names.

01:08:03.629 --> 01:08:05.715 line:80%
I was not sure which one you would prefer.

01:08:05.798 --> 01:08:06.841 line:80%
[chuckles]

01:08:08.676 --> 01:08:10.052 line:80%
Why did you seek me so earnestly?

01:08:26.068 --> 01:08:27.153 line:80%
I wanted to propose.

01:08:32.992 --> 01:08:33.993 line:80%
Let's…

01:08:35.912 --> 01:08:36.913 line:80%
get married.

01:08:41.250 --> 01:08:43.461 line:80%
[♪ uplifting music playing]

01:09:04.148 --> 01:09:07.068 line:80%
PERFECT CROWN

01:09:08.402 --> 01:09:10.905 line:80%
[♪ pop music playing]

01:09:43.187 --> 01:09:44.480 line:80%
Let's…

01:09:44.981 --> 01:09:46.107 line:80%
get married.

01:09:46.190 --> 01:09:48.985 line:80%
<i>My pedigree is impressive,</i>
<i>and my acumen sharper still.</i>

01:09:49.068 --> 01:09:50.069 line:80%
[I-AN] <i>I decline.</i>

01:09:50.861 --> 01:09:52.321 line:80%
[Huiju] <i>I was rejected.</i>

01:09:52.405 --> 01:09:54.031 line:80%
-<i>I missed you.</i>
-Seong Huiju?

01:09:54.115 --> 01:09:55.282 line:80%
Hyah!

01:09:55.366 --> 01:09:57.201 line:80%
You dared to run a background check on me?

01:09:57.284 --> 01:09:58.661 line:80%
-Yes.
-"Yes"?

01:09:58.744 --> 01:09:59.912 line:80%
[giggles]

01:09:59.996 --> 01:10:01.580 line:80%
[Yun] <i>I must meet this maiden.</i>

01:10:02.957 --> 01:10:05.751 line:20%
[Huiju]
<i>"Grand Prince I-AN's secret lover"?</i>

01:10:05.835 --> 01:10:06.961 line:20%
<i>Me?</i>

01:10:07.545 --> 01:10:10.172 line:20%
-<i>They're even speculating you're pregnant.</i>
-[in English] What?

01:10:10.256 --> 01:10:14.051 line:20%
[I-AN, in Korean] You would marry me
for nothing more than a hollow title?

01:10:19.598 --> 01:10:23.477 line:20%
EPILOGUE

01:10:23.561 --> 01:10:25.563 line:20%
[♪ gentle music playing]

01:11:16.113 --> 01:11:18.532 line:20%
And considering how easily
you secured this approval,

01:11:19.450 --> 01:11:21.535 line:20%
I guess it was only out of reach for me.

01:11:21.619 --> 01:11:24.413 line:20%
So do not lecture me
about demerit points or whatever.

01:11:34.882 --> 01:11:36.801 line:20%
I'm so screwed.

01:11:38.844 --> 01:11:40.137 line:20%
Am I going to get expelled?

01:11:41.180 --> 01:11:46.352 line:20%
What if I end up in prison
for insulting the royal family?

01:11:46.435 --> 01:11:48.229 line:20%
Why on earth did I do that?

01:11:48.854 --> 01:11:50.189 line:20%
[groans]

01:11:50.272 --> 01:11:52.066 line:20%
Hey, get up.

01:11:52.149 --> 01:11:53.984 line:20%
Hurry, get up. There's an announcement.

01:11:54.068 --> 01:11:55.569 line:20%
What announcement?

01:11:55.653 --> 01:11:57.071 line:20%
Get up. Hurry.

01:11:57.154 --> 01:11:58.989 line:20%
It's total chaos. Everyone's freaking out.

01:11:59.073 --> 01:12:00.074 line:20%
Why?

01:12:00.157 --> 01:12:02.576 line:20%
[students clamoring]

01:12:08.624 --> 01:12:10.376 line:80%
[principal] <i>As Confucius said,</i>

01:12:10.960 --> 01:12:13.087 line:20%
"Though a noble man
does not contend with others,

01:12:13.170 --> 01:12:15.506 line:20%
he must compete when it comes to archery."

01:12:18.050 --> 01:12:20.094 line:20%
[I-AN]
<i>The forthcoming exhibition match</i>

01:12:20.177 --> 01:12:21.554 line:20%
<i>celebrates that spirit.</i>

01:12:22.721 --> 01:12:25.808 line:20%
<i>Thus, students shall devote themselves</i>
<i>to their training.</i>

01:12:26.600 --> 01:12:28.435 line:20%
Well? Isn't this amazing?

01:12:28.519 --> 01:12:30.354 line:20%
The range will be open for a whole month.

01:12:30.896 --> 01:12:32.940 line:20%
You said you didn't have
enough time to train.

01:12:35.568 --> 01:12:37.278 line:80%
[I-AN]
<i>The sole condition for access</i>

01:12:38.237 --> 01:12:39.280 line:20%
<i>shall be the observance</i>

01:12:40.281 --> 01:12:42.032 line:20%
<i>of protocol and decorum.</i>

01:12:51.917 --> 01:12:53.919 line:20%
Translated by Justin S. Kim

01:13:05.222 --> 01:13:08.934 line:80%
PERFECT CROWN